WEBVTT

00:02.519 --> 00:04.728
♪ ♪

00:28.959 --> 00:31.134
♪ ♪

00:34.482 --> 00:37.244
HICCUP:
<i>This is Berk.</i>

00:37.382 --> 00:41.558
<i>So far off the map that</i>
<i>it might as well not exist.</i>

00:42.904 --> 00:44.285
<i>My village?</i>

00:44.423 --> 00:46.632
<i>In a word, sturdy.</i>

00:46.770 --> 00:48.151
<i> </i><i>It’s been here for generations,</i>

00:48.289 --> 00:50.878
<i>but every single building</i>
<i>is new.</i>

00:51.016 --> 00:52.604
<i>The air is crisp,</i>
<i>the water is clean,</i>

00:52.742 --> 00:55.365
<i>and the views are nothing</i>
<i>to complain about.</i>

00:55.503 --> 00:58.403
<i>The only downsides</i>
<i>are the pests.</i>

01:04.409 --> 01:05.962
[bell clanging]

01:06.100 --> 01:09.310
<i>You see, most places</i>
<i>have mice or mosquitoes.</i>

01:09.448 --> 01:10.622
<i>We have...</i>

01:10.760 --> 01:12.072
[flame whooshing]

01:12.210 --> 01:14.626
[grunts, whimpers]

01:14.764 --> 01:16.593
[panting]

01:16.731 --> 01:18.561
Dragons.

01:18.699 --> 01:20.114
[groans]

01:20.942 --> 01:22.289
[frantic chatter]

01:22.427 --> 01:24.670
HICCUP:
<i>Most people would leave.</i>

01:24.808 --> 01:26.224
<i>Not us.</i>

01:26.362 --> 01:27.984
<i>We’re Vikings.</i>

01:28.122 --> 01:29.917
<i>We don’t run from fights.</i>
<i>We start them.</i>

01:30.055 --> 01:31.677
- Hey! Hiccup!
- Evening.

01:31.815 --> 01:32.851
Go home!

01:32.989 --> 01:34.301
I will just as soon as I, uh...

01:34.439 --> 01:36.751
You’re in the way again!

01:36.889 --> 01:39.375
♪ ♪

01:39.513 --> 01:41.101
VIKING:
Hiccup, play dead!

01:41.239 --> 01:42.757
HICCUP:
<i>You see, dragons have been</i>

01:42.895 --> 01:44.276
<i>a bit of a problem.</i>

01:44.414 --> 01:46.830
<i>Here and, well, everywhere.</i>

01:46.968 --> 01:50.144
<i>So we decided to take</i>
<i>the fight to them.</i>

01:50.282 --> 01:52.836
- <i> </i><i>-How’s that working out for us?</i>
<i>- [sheep bleats, squeals]</i>

01:52.974 --> 01:54.631
<i>Eh...</i>

01:57.496 --> 01:58.601
- [explosive whooshing]
- [gasps]

01:58.739 --> 02:00.327
- Whoa!
- What are you doing?

02:00.465 --> 02:02.984
- What is he doing out again?
- [chuckling]

02:03.123 --> 02:04.814
- Get inside. Go on.
- [grunts]

02:04.952 --> 02:07.541
HICCUP:
<i>That’s Stoick the Vast,</i>

02:07.679 --> 02:08.818
<i>chief of the tribe.</i>

02:08.956 --> 02:10.647
[screaming]

02:10.785 --> 02:12.546
<i>They say, when he was a baby,</i>

02:12.684 --> 02:14.996
<i>he popped a dragon’s head</i>
<i>clean off its shoulders.</i>

02:15.135 --> 02:16.998
<i>- Do I believe it?</i>
- [yells]

02:18.517 --> 02:20.416
<i>- Yes, I do.</i>
- What have we got?

02:20.554 --> 02:24.144
Gronckles, Nadders,
Zipplebacks, Skrills.

02:24.282 --> 02:26.146
Snorti spotted
a Monstrous Nightmare.

02:26.284 --> 02:27.388
Any Night Furies?

02:27.526 --> 02:28.700
None so far, Chief.

02:28.838 --> 02:30.598
Good.

02:30.736 --> 02:32.359
- Follow me.
- HÜRL: Right, Chief.

02:32.497 --> 02:34.395
STOICK:
Come on, you wretches!

02:34.533 --> 02:36.535
HÜRL:
You heard him. Come on, lads.

02:36.673 --> 02:38.848
♪ ♪

02:39.814 --> 02:41.333
Oh. Out again?

02:41.471 --> 02:43.301
HICCUP:
Just pretend I’m not even here.

02:43.439 --> 02:45.199
I’ll be in and out
before you can say...

02:45.337 --> 02:47.236
Not so fast.

02:47.374 --> 02:48.651
[groans] Come on, please.

02:48.789 --> 02:50.549
<i>The meathead with attitude</i>

02:50.687 --> 02:52.551
<i>and interchangeable hands</i>
<i>is Gobber.</i>

02:52.689 --> 02:53.966
Here. Go on.

02:54.104 --> 02:55.934
HICCUP:
<i>I’ve been his apprentice</i>

02:56.072 --> 02:57.556
<i>- ever since I was little.</i>
- I’m keeping my eye on you.

02:57.694 --> 02:59.040
I’m not even supposed
to be out here.

02:59.179 --> 03:01.595
Ha! Since when did that
ever stop you?

03:01.733 --> 03:04.356
[clamoring]

03:04.494 --> 03:05.875
STOICK:
Guard the food stores.

03:06.013 --> 03:07.877
- Aye, Chief.
- Protect the livestock.

03:08.015 --> 03:09.223
HÜRL:
Aye, Stoick.

03:09.361 --> 03:11.121
And keep an ear out
for Night Furies.

03:18.991 --> 03:20.061
[screaming]

03:20.200 --> 03:21.891
GOBBER:
Hammer.

03:24.100 --> 03:26.723
- [flame whooshing]
- [Vikings screaming]

03:29.105 --> 03:30.555
TUFFNUT:
Fire brigade!

03:30.693 --> 03:32.246
HICCUP:
<i>Ah, the fire brigade.</i>

03:32.384 --> 03:34.144
<i>Berk’s cool kids.</i>

03:34.283 --> 03:37.286
<i>They get to be out</i>
<i>in the action.</i>

03:37.424 --> 03:39.391
ASTRID:
Guys, out of the way!

03:40.254 --> 03:41.600
HICCUP:
<i>But they’re nothing</i>

03:41.738 --> 03:43.084
<i>without their captain,</i>

03:43.223 --> 03:45.949
<i>the shining star</i>
<i>of our generation.</i>

03:46.087 --> 03:48.987
<i> </i><i>A-Amazing without even trying.</i>

03:49.125 --> 03:51.507
<i>The one that smokes them all.</i>

03:52.715 --> 03:55.096
<i>[sighs] Astrid.</i>

03:55.235 --> 03:58.065
♪ ♪

04:08.248 --> 04:09.904
What?

04:10.042 --> 04:11.699
Uh...

04:11.837 --> 04:14.254
Shouldn’t you be in bed?
[laughs]

04:15.185 --> 04:16.325
[sighs]

04:16.463 --> 04:18.016
GOBBER:
Come on, back to work.

04:19.259 --> 04:20.777
You know,
I need to get out there.

04:20.915 --> 04:22.710
Show my stuff, make my mark.

04:22.848 --> 04:25.299
You’ve made plenty of marks,
all in the wrong places.

04:25.437 --> 04:27.474
Give me two minutes.
I’ll-I’ll take down a dragon.

04:27.612 --> 04:30.304
My life will get
infinitely better.

04:30.442 --> 04:31.926
I might even get a girlfriend.

04:32.064 --> 04:33.342
VIKING: There’s a Zippleback
behind you!

04:33.480 --> 04:34.826
Astrid? [laughs]

04:34.964 --> 04:36.448
But she’s a real Viking.

04:36.586 --> 04:37.829
You can’t wield a hammer.

04:37.967 --> 04:39.658
You can’t swing an axe.

04:39.796 --> 04:41.488
You can’t even throw
one of these.

04:41.626 --> 04:43.938
See, but this...
this will throw it for me.

04:44.076 --> 04:46.147
- Oh, another one.
- It’s fully redesigned.

04:46.286 --> 04:47.701
It-it’s...

04:47.839 --> 04:49.289
- Whoa!
- Whew!

04:49.427 --> 04:51.325
- HICCUP: It’s, uh...
- [groans]

04:51.463 --> 04:53.569
double-barreled.

04:53.707 --> 04:55.881
You see, this right here...
this is what I’m talking about.

04:56.019 --> 04:58.367
Okay, this is a mild cal...
mild calibration issue.

04:58.505 --> 05:00.334
If you ever want
to get out there

05:00.472 --> 05:03.337
and start fighting dragons,
you’ve got to stop all of...

05:03.475 --> 05:04.994
all of this.

05:05.132 --> 05:06.306
You just gestured to all of me.

05:06.444 --> 05:08.963
Yeah. Stop being all of you.

05:09.101 --> 05:10.689
Oh...

05:10.827 --> 05:12.104
Oh, yeah.

05:12.242 --> 05:14.521
You, sir, are playing
a dangerous game.

05:14.659 --> 05:16.661
- [gasping]
- Keeping this contained?

05:16.799 --> 05:18.352
- There will be consequences.
- [grunts]

05:18.490 --> 05:21.769
Well, I will take my chances.

05:22.667 --> 05:25.221
Sword-- sharpen. Now.

05:26.809 --> 05:29.570
HICCUP:
<i>One day, I’ll get out there.</i>

05:29.708 --> 05:33.678
<i>Because killing a dragon</i>
<i>is everything around here.</i>

05:34.713 --> 05:36.370
<i>Gronckles are tough.</i>

05:36.508 --> 05:39.477
<i>Taking one down </i><i> </i>
<i>would at least get me noticed.</i>

05:41.720 --> 05:43.619
<i>- A Zippleback?</i>
- [frantic shouting]

05:43.757 --> 05:46.000
<i>Exotic, exciting.</i>

05:47.243 --> 05:49.659
<i>Two heads, twice the status.</i>

05:50.695 --> 05:52.282
<i>Lopping off a Nadder’s head</i>

05:52.421 --> 05:54.008
<i>would definitely show them</i>
<i>I belong.</i>

05:54.146 --> 05:55.562
[snarling]

05:57.978 --> 06:00.221
- [sheep bleating]
- [dragon snarling]

06:00.360 --> 06:01.533
VIKING:
Come on, lads!

06:01.671 --> 06:03.259
RETCHA:
They found the sheep.

06:03.397 --> 06:05.986
Then let loose
with everything we’ve got.

06:09.886 --> 06:11.543
HICCUP:
<i>And then there’s</i>

06:11.681 --> 06:13.442
<i>the Monstrous Nightmare.</i>

06:13.580 --> 06:15.098
[roars]

06:15.616 --> 06:17.238
Reload!

06:17.377 --> 06:18.757
HICCUP: <i>Only the best Vikings</i>
<i>go after those.</i>

06:18.895 --> 06:21.864
- [grunting]
- [dragon snarling, screeching]

06:24.729 --> 06:26.282
<i>But the ultimate prize</i>

06:26.420 --> 06:29.492
<i>is the dragon</i>
<i>that no one has ever seen.</i>

06:29.630 --> 06:31.943
<i>- We call it the...</i>
- Night Fury!

06:32.081 --> 06:33.807
- Jump!
- [whooshing]

06:37.431 --> 06:39.709
GOBBER:
And we’ve got a Night Fury.

06:39.847 --> 06:43.575
Never steals food,
never shows itself.

06:43.713 --> 06:45.543
And never misses.

06:46.716 --> 06:48.442
[grunts]

06:48.580 --> 06:50.271
Time for old Gobber
to take over.

06:50.410 --> 06:52.791
- [flame whooshing]
- [indistinct shouting]

06:52.929 --> 06:54.517
Stay put here.

06:54.655 --> 06:56.312
Here. I’m serious.

06:56.450 --> 06:58.418
HICCUP: <i>No one has</i>
<i>ever killed a Night Fury.</i>

06:58.556 --> 07:00.420
GOBBER:
Attack!

07:00.558 --> 07:02.767
HICCUP: <i>That’s why</i>
<i>I’m going to be the first.</i>

07:04.907 --> 07:07.185
- You again? Get back inside!
- I’ll make a point of it.

07:07.323 --> 07:08.945
LOOGI: You’re going to get
yourself killed, Hiccup!

07:09.083 --> 07:10.982
HICCUP:
I know! Sorry.

07:12.673 --> 07:15.400
[sheep bleating]

07:15.538 --> 07:17.920
Here, give me that. [grunts]

07:18.058 --> 07:20.094
[squeals]

07:20.957 --> 07:22.442
[grunting]

07:22.580 --> 07:24.374
Mind yourself!

07:24.513 --> 07:27.101
This Nadder still has
some fire in it.

07:27.239 --> 07:29.483
♪ ♪

07:37.318 --> 07:39.148
[whispering]:
Come on.

07:39.286 --> 07:41.530
Give me something to shoot at.
Give me something to shoot at.

07:43.670 --> 07:45.465
Come on, show yourself.

07:48.537 --> 07:50.918
[whooshing]

07:54.301 --> 07:55.475
[grunts]

07:57.235 --> 07:59.617
- [dragon screeching]
- I hit it.

08:03.793 --> 08:04.829
[shouts excitedly]

08:04.967 --> 08:06.520
- I hit it!
- [growling]

08:06.658 --> 08:09.040
Did anybody see that?

08:10.179 --> 08:11.698
Except for you.

08:12.526 --> 08:15.011
[Hiccup screaming]

08:15.149 --> 08:17.013
HICCUP:
Oh, gods. [screams]

08:18.359 --> 08:21.708
Spitelout,
do not let that escape.

08:21.846 --> 08:23.606
[sighs] Thanks a lot.

08:23.744 --> 08:25.366
[grunting]

08:27.748 --> 08:29.060
[whimpers]

08:40.865 --> 08:42.901
[dragon snarling]

08:45.214 --> 08:47.147
[screeches]

08:48.700 --> 08:50.150
STOICK:
You’re all out.

08:50.288 --> 08:52.911
Let’s see what else
you’re made of.

08:54.568 --> 08:56.812
[grunting fiercely]

09:10.342 --> 09:12.759
Aye, that’s what I thought.

09:14.657 --> 09:17.591
HICCUP: <i>Oh, and there’s one</i>
<i>more thing to know.</i>

09:17.729 --> 09:20.145
[creaking]

09:20.283 --> 09:22.044
VIKING:
Look out!

09:25.219 --> 09:27.428
[whimpers]

09:28.257 --> 09:29.569
[sighs]

09:31.467 --> 09:34.228
Sorry, Dad.

09:36.265 --> 09:38.612
- SPITELOUT: Watch out!
- [yelling]

09:39.993 --> 09:41.546
[sheep squeals]

09:41.684 --> 09:43.444
[sheep bleating]

09:43.583 --> 09:45.757
♪ ♪

09:48.760 --> 09:49.968
[sighs]

09:50.106 --> 09:51.970
Okay, but I hit a Night Fury.

09:52.108 --> 09:53.489
[Stoick grunts]

09:53.627 --> 09:54.973
Dad, this isn’t like
any other time.

09:55.111 --> 09:56.526
I mean, I really hit one.

09:56.665 --> 09:59.081
Aye, a dragon
no one’s ever seen.

09:59.219 --> 10:01.152
Because it uses night
as its camouflage.

10:01.290 --> 10:03.464
If you squint, you can see it
blotting out the stars.

10:03.603 --> 10:06.467
- That’s how I shot it down.
- Stop!

10:07.365 --> 10:08.780
Stop.

10:09.816 --> 10:12.508
Every time you step outside,
disaster happens.

10:12.646 --> 10:16.788
Can you not see
that I have bigger problems?

10:16.926 --> 10:18.134
Winter is almost here,

10:18.272 --> 10:20.654
and I have an entire village
to feed.

10:20.792 --> 10:22.345
Between you and me,
the village could do

10:22.483 --> 10:24.313
with a little less feeding.

10:24.451 --> 10:26.729
This isn’t a joke, Hiccup!

10:26.867 --> 10:29.698
Why can’t you follow
the simplest orders?

10:29.836 --> 10:31.872
Because I can’t stop myself.

10:32.010 --> 10:36.290
Okay? I see a dragon,
and I have to just... kill it.

10:36.428 --> 10:38.499
You know, i-it’s...
it’s who I am.

10:38.638 --> 10:40.191
[sighs]

10:40.329 --> 10:42.676
You are many things, son,

10:42.814 --> 10:45.610
but a dragon killer
is not one of them.

10:48.855 --> 10:50.960
Get back to the house.

10:51.098 --> 10:52.928
Make sure he stays there.

10:53.756 --> 10:55.516
How much can
one person mess up?

10:55.655 --> 10:58.036
Anyone else would have been
booted off the island by now.

10:58.174 --> 11:01.039
I guess being son of the chief
has its privileges.

11:02.178 --> 11:04.111
If not for the chief, though...

11:05.043 --> 11:09.461
[grunts] Anyway, my dad’s
super proud of me, so...

11:09.599 --> 11:10.911
[sighs]

11:11.049 --> 11:12.085
[laughing]:
Dad, I was just talking...

11:12.223 --> 11:13.707
Don’t talk to me in public.

11:13.845 --> 11:15.329
[chuckles]

11:15.467 --> 11:16.986
HICCUP:
You know, I really did hit one.

11:17.124 --> 11:18.574
GOBBER:
Of course you did, Hiccup.

11:18.712 --> 11:19.886
He never listens.

11:20.024 --> 11:21.232
Well, that runs in the family.

11:21.370 --> 11:23.510
And-and when he does,

11:23.648 --> 11:26.202
it’s always with
some disappointed scowl,

11:26.340 --> 11:27.963
like somebody forgot
the meat in the stew.

11:28.101 --> 11:29.619
[chuckles] I’ve seen that look.

11:29.758 --> 11:34.141
Oi. You’re thinking
about this all wrong, eh?

11:34.279 --> 11:36.419
It’s not so much
what you look like.

11:36.557 --> 11:38.974
It’s what’s inside of you
he can’t stand.

11:40.147 --> 11:42.253
Thank you for summing that up.

11:42.391 --> 11:45.290
W-Wait. The point is...

11:45.428 --> 11:48.362
stop trying so hard
to be something you’re not.

11:50.226 --> 11:52.608
I just want to be
one of you guys.

11:54.472 --> 11:56.508
[door closes]

11:59.511 --> 12:01.065
I know you do.

12:02.687 --> 12:04.862
♪ ♪

12:19.600 --> 12:21.775
[clamoring]

12:27.919 --> 12:31.681
No one said it would be easy!

12:31.820 --> 12:33.304
[clamoring stops]

12:33.442 --> 12:35.133
But may I remind you,

12:35.271 --> 12:40.104
we are all descendants
of the finest dragon fighters

12:40.242 --> 12:43.555
from everywhere
Vikings have traveled,

12:43.693 --> 12:46.110
who gathered here
because they knew

12:46.248 --> 12:48.457
that we were within
spitting distance

12:48.595 --> 12:51.425
of a key dragon’s nest.

12:52.357 --> 12:54.187
If we can just take it,

12:54.325 --> 12:56.672
we can wipe out the devils
for good.

12:56.810 --> 12:59.192
Take it? We can’t even find it.

12:59.330 --> 13:00.400
- [murmuring]
- RETCHA: Exactly.

13:00.538 --> 13:01.781
This nest is starting to sound

13:01.919 --> 13:03.299
more and more
like a fairy tale.

13:03.437 --> 13:04.818
We’re exhausted.

13:04.956 --> 13:06.268
And what do we have
to show for it, eh?

13:06.406 --> 13:07.614
VIKINGS:
Nothing!

13:07.752 --> 13:08.822
We have purpose.

13:08.960 --> 13:10.651
- [laughter]
- Oh, come on.

13:10.790 --> 13:14.034
We are the warriors of Berk,

13:14.172 --> 13:17.866
the roughest, toughest tribe
this side of the sun.

13:19.384 --> 13:21.524
No? [scoffs]

13:21.662 --> 13:23.388
Phlegma.

13:23.526 --> 13:27.876
We watched you take down
a Zippleback singlehandedly.

13:28.014 --> 13:30.361
I mean, sure, you lost your leg
in the process,

13:30.499 --> 13:33.053
but you came out on top,
didn’t you?

13:33.191 --> 13:34.537
- Well... [stammers]
- STOICK: Yes, you did.

13:34.675 --> 13:38.162
Retcha, your people came
from the Far East.

13:38.300 --> 13:41.648
Fungi, yours all the way
from-from the Silk Road.

13:41.786 --> 13:43.650
Loogi, your people came

13:43.788 --> 13:46.377
from the sunbaked coasts
of Bláland.

13:46.515 --> 13:47.999
And look at us.

13:48.137 --> 13:50.001
We’re still here.
We’re still fighting.

13:50.139 --> 13:53.315
We’re still watching
each other’s backs.

13:53.453 --> 13:56.180
So are we really gonna pack up
and go home

13:56.318 --> 13:57.871
while these bloody beasts

13:58.009 --> 14:01.737
are still a threat
to all of our lands?

14:01.875 --> 14:03.256
Is that who we are?

14:03.394 --> 14:05.120
- VIKINGS: No.
- Is it?

14:05.258 --> 14:06.638
- No.
- Is it?!

14:06.776 --> 14:07.639
No!

14:07.777 --> 14:08.917
Is it?!

14:09.055 --> 14:10.677
No!

14:10.815 --> 14:11.747
Is it?

14:11.885 --> 14:14.232
Uh, no, Chief, I guess not.

14:14.370 --> 14:16.372
That’s what I thought.

14:19.444 --> 14:22.862
Elder Gothi, give us a sign.

14:23.000 --> 14:25.692
Do we stand a chance
of finding the nest

14:25.830 --> 14:27.590
before the ice sets in?

14:46.437 --> 14:48.818
Then that’s all I need.

14:51.028 --> 14:54.065
Back into the fog we go.

14:54.203 --> 14:55.411
All right, everyone.

14:55.549 --> 14:57.275
- Prepare the ships!
- [cheering]

14:57.413 --> 14:58.311
Let’s go!

14:58.449 --> 14:59.899
♪ ♪

15:09.391 --> 15:12.946
Do I take my bucket hand
for when they burn our ships

15:13.084 --> 15:16.536
or my swimming hand
for when they sink them?

15:20.920 --> 15:23.267
STOICK:
Not so fast, Gobber.

15:24.993 --> 15:27.857
I don’t have time to train
this year’s recruits,

15:27.996 --> 15:29.100
so you’ll do it.

15:29.238 --> 15:30.791
Ah, the old rite of passage.

15:30.930 --> 15:32.932
Hiccup’s just come of age,
hasn’t he?

15:33.070 --> 15:35.037
[scoffs] I meant the others.

15:35.175 --> 15:37.557
Yeah, so while I’m busy,
he’ll c-cover the stall.

15:37.695 --> 15:40.353
Molten steel,
razor-sharp blades,

15:40.491 --> 15:41.526
lots of time on his hands.

15:41.664 --> 15:42.976
What could possibly go wrong?

15:43.114 --> 15:44.667
Oh, what am I gonna do
with him, Gobber?

15:44.805 --> 15:47.256
[sighs] Stick him in training.

15:47.394 --> 15:49.155
No. I’m serious.

15:49.293 --> 15:50.673
Yeah, so am I.

15:50.811 --> 15:52.917
The kid wants this
more than anything.

15:53.055 --> 15:54.988
- [Stoick scoffs]
- Believe it or not,

15:55.126 --> 15:57.163
that young man actually
wants to make you proud.

15:57.301 --> 15:59.717
But he’s got a mind of his own.

15:59.855 --> 16:01.719
Gets that from his mother.
[scoffs]

16:01.857 --> 16:03.307
Look what happened to her.

16:03.445 --> 16:04.791
Yeah, ’cause Valka was
the stubborn one.

16:04.929 --> 16:06.724
- See, when I was a boy...
- Oh, here we go.

16:06.862 --> 16:09.071
I-I followed orders.
Right? I worked hard.

16:09.209 --> 16:12.212
Because I believed
in what a-a Viking could do.

16:12.350 --> 16:14.352
Crush mountains,

16:14.490 --> 16:17.148
level forests, tame seas.

16:17.286 --> 16:21.187
I knew what I was
and what I had to become.

16:22.015 --> 16:25.674
Hiccup is... he’s not that boy.

16:25.812 --> 16:30.196
What chance does he have
of following in my footsteps?

16:30.334 --> 16:31.714
GOBBER:
Yeah.

16:31.852 --> 16:33.199
[Stoick sighs]

16:36.340 --> 16:38.652
You can’t stop him, Stoick.

16:38.790 --> 16:40.758
You can only prepare him.

16:40.896 --> 16:42.484
Because the truth is

16:42.622 --> 16:44.658
we aren’t always gonna
be around to protect him.

16:45.556 --> 16:47.592
He’s gonna get out there again.

16:47.730 --> 16:50.457
[chuckles]
He’s probably out there now.

16:52.459 --> 16:56.049
♪ ♪

16:56.187 --> 16:58.362
[birds chirping]

17:11.996 --> 17:14.033
[sighs]

17:15.896 --> 17:17.588
[grunts]

17:18.416 --> 17:20.660
[yells]

17:22.144 --> 17:25.423
How could I lose
an entire dragon?!

17:25.561 --> 17:27.115
[grunts]

17:28.875 --> 17:31.050
♪ ♪

17:46.513 --> 17:48.101
[gasps]

17:51.656 --> 17:53.865
♪ ♪

18:08.052 --> 18:10.434
[panting sharply]

18:23.240 --> 18:25.104
[chuckles softly]

18:25.966 --> 18:27.244
I did it.

18:29.280 --> 18:30.523
I did it!

18:30.661 --> 18:33.595
- [dragon groaning]
- [gasps]

18:37.116 --> 18:39.325
[panting]

18:39.463 --> 18:42.190
Oh, why couldn’t you
have been dead?

18:44.330 --> 18:46.608
Now I have to kill you.

18:48.644 --> 18:50.853
♪ ♪

18:52.648 --> 18:54.478
[dragon groans softly]

18:56.238 --> 18:58.654
[Hiccup panting sharply]

19:05.627 --> 19:07.111
[whimpers]

19:07.905 --> 19:10.528
[groaning]

19:13.462 --> 19:15.395
[groans]

19:22.575 --> 19:24.335
[sighs]

19:26.372 --> 19:28.512
[dragon groaning]

19:42.698 --> 19:44.735
[dragon moans in pain]

19:48.256 --> 19:50.119
[takes deep breath]

19:51.604 --> 19:54.986
[blade slicing through ropes]

19:56.125 --> 19:57.541
[roars]

19:57.679 --> 19:59.853
[growling]

19:59.991 --> 20:01.890
[gasping breaths]

20:07.206 --> 20:09.346
[high-pitched roaring]

20:12.418 --> 20:14.385
[exhales sharply]

20:15.421 --> 20:17.906
[roaring]

20:26.052 --> 20:28.192
[dragon squealing in distance]

20:28.330 --> 20:29.745
[sighs]

20:44.173 --> 20:45.416
Hiccup.

20:46.624 --> 20:49.248
Dad. Uh...

20:50.904 --> 20:53.597
Look, I need
to talk to you, Dad.

20:55.530 --> 20:58.153
I need to speak
with you, too, son.

21:00.466 --> 21:01.846
I’ve decided I don’t want

21:01.984 --> 21:02.951
- to fight dragons.
- I think it’s time

21:03.089 --> 21:03.814
you learn to fight dragons.

21:03.952 --> 21:04.780
BOTH:
What?

21:04.918 --> 21:06.057
Well, you go first.

21:06.195 --> 21:07.473
No, no, no, no.
You-you go first.

21:07.611 --> 21:09.958
You get your wish.

21:10.096 --> 21:11.442
Dragon training.

21:11.580 --> 21:13.237
Start in the morning.

21:14.894 --> 21:16.620
Oh, man, I really
should’ve gone first.

21:16.758 --> 21:18.518
You know,
’cause I-I was thinking,

21:18.656 --> 21:21.314
we have a surplus
of dragon-fighting Vikings,

21:21.452 --> 21:23.040
but do we have enough
bread-making Vikings or...

21:23.178 --> 21:24.524
You’ll need this.

21:25.318 --> 21:28.148
Dad... I don’t want
to fight dragons.

21:28.287 --> 21:29.633
[laughing]:
Come on.

21:29.771 --> 21:31.324
Yes, you do.

21:31.462 --> 21:32.877
No, let me rephrase.

21:33.015 --> 21:34.638
I can’t kill dragons.

21:34.776 --> 21:36.260
But you will.

21:36.398 --> 21:38.538
No, I’m very extra sure
that I won’t.

21:38.676 --> 21:41.610
It’s time, Hiccup.

21:43.819 --> 21:46.374
Uh... can you not hear me?

21:46.512 --> 21:48.859
Can you not hear me?!

21:54.658 --> 21:58.040
The Trial of Flame is
where Vikings are made.

21:58.834 --> 22:03.460
Where heroes are forged,
where future chiefs are born.

22:04.357 --> 22:07.222
I... I’m none of those things.

22:08.568 --> 22:10.743
I’m not like you, Dad.

22:10.881 --> 22:13.124
♪ ♪

22:13.953 --> 22:15.817
[sighs]

22:15.955 --> 22:17.646
Listen.

22:21.029 --> 22:23.756
When you carry this axe,

22:23.894 --> 22:26.034
you carry all of us with you.

22:26.172 --> 22:27.898
Which means you walk like us,

22:28.036 --> 22:31.384
you talk like us,
you think like us.

22:31.522 --> 22:35.284
No more of... this.

22:36.113 --> 22:38.218
You just gestured to all of me.

22:38.357 --> 22:39.806
Deal?

22:39.944 --> 22:41.394
This conversation is feeling
very one-sided.

22:41.532 --> 22:43.879
Deal?

22:45.985 --> 22:47.193
Deal.

22:47.331 --> 22:48.884
Good.

22:51.715 --> 22:53.372
[sighs]

22:55.028 --> 22:56.409
Train hard.

22:58.618 --> 23:00.413
I’ll be back.

23:03.865 --> 23:05.418
Probably.

23:08.041 --> 23:09.836
[door closes]

23:09.974 --> 23:11.769
And I’ll be here.

23:13.461 --> 23:15.048
Maybe.

23:17.085 --> 23:19.156
♪ ♪

23:19.294 --> 23:22.953
GOBBER:
Welcome to the Trial of Flame.

23:36.484 --> 23:39.418
SNOTLOUT: The moment
we’ve all been waiting for.

23:39.556 --> 23:41.972
I just got to pick a spot
for my statue.

23:42.110 --> 23:43.974
It’s so much bigger
from down here.

23:44.112 --> 23:46.597
Can you guys believe
we’re actually standing here?

23:46.735 --> 23:49.911
This is where Chief Greybile
slew the Whispering Death.

23:50.049 --> 23:51.153
Yeah, and it’s where
Chief Tuffnut

23:51.291 --> 23:52.603
will slay everything else.

23:52.741 --> 23:53.984
- Watch and learn.
- Man, I can’t wait

23:54.122 --> 23:55.882
to get some
legendary war wounds!

23:56.020 --> 23:58.644
Yeah, like a nasty gash
right across my face.

23:58.782 --> 24:00.059
- Call me boring...
- Boring.

24:00.197 --> 24:01.578
...but I’m just excited to see

24:01.716 --> 24:03.959
some real live dragons
up close.

24:04.097 --> 24:07.031
You know, I could do without
the permanent injuries and...

24:07.169 --> 24:08.792
Oh, where’s the glory in that?

24:08.930 --> 24:10.379
Yeah, it’s only fun
if you get a scar out of it.

24:10.518 --> 24:12.830
HICCUP [chuckling]:
I know, right?

24:13.797 --> 24:14.763
Pain.

24:14.901 --> 24:16.109
Love it.

24:16.247 --> 24:18.042
Oh, great. Who let him in?

24:18.180 --> 24:20.666
Mm, I guess Daddy pulled
some strings, huh?

24:20.804 --> 24:22.495
Aren’t you two, like,
a little old to be here?

24:22.633 --> 24:24.186
- Ouch.
- Wait, what did you say, whippersnapper?

24:24.324 --> 24:25.464
What did you say?
Can you say it again?

24:26.637 --> 24:28.190
Yeah, touchy subject.

24:28.328 --> 24:30.020
They’ve flunked dragon training
a few times.

24:30.158 --> 24:31.987
Um, it was four times,
actually.

24:32.125 --> 24:33.782
Yeah, and it’s called
being held back.

24:33.920 --> 24:35.853
As in too valuable
to let go of.

24:35.991 --> 24:38.373
Real sensitive, Hiccup.

24:38.511 --> 24:39.892
Nice name, by the way.

24:40.030 --> 24:41.652
Your name is Snotlout.

24:41.790 --> 24:42.757
Exactly.

24:42.895 --> 24:44.931
It’s a manly Viking name.

24:45.069 --> 24:46.346
Translates from
the ancient texts as

24:46.485 --> 24:48.003
"one who beateth the snot
out of a..."

24:48.141 --> 24:49.557
GOBBER:
Shut up.

24:49.695 --> 24:51.041
Let’s get started.

24:51.179 --> 24:52.905
Bloody kids.

24:53.802 --> 24:57.357
You are now the latest to join
this time-honored tradition.

24:57.496 --> 24:59.532
Every toe biter
born into our tribe

24:59.670 --> 25:01.707
must one day survive this arena

25:01.845 --> 25:04.951
if they ever hope to do battle
alongside the rest of us.

25:06.021 --> 25:08.023
It will be grueling.

25:10.198 --> 25:13.891
And it will be
very, very dangerous.

25:14.892 --> 25:19.241
But whoever does best will win
the title of Top Slayer.

25:20.691 --> 25:23.038
And with it...

25:23.176 --> 25:26.559
And with it, the honor
of killing their first dragon

25:26.697 --> 25:29.148
in front of the entire village.

25:29.286 --> 25:31.253
There is no greater glory.

25:32.496 --> 25:33.773
What?

25:33.911 --> 25:35.603
Hiccup already killed
a Night Fury,

25:35.741 --> 25:38.019
so does that, like, what,
disqualify him or...

25:38.157 --> 25:40.504
GOBBER:
Oh, ignore him.

25:40.642 --> 25:42.057
You’re skinny.

25:42.195 --> 25:43.611
You’re weak.

25:43.749 --> 25:45.820
That’ll make you
less of a target.

25:45.958 --> 25:47.304
They’ll see you
as slim pickings.

25:47.442 --> 25:48.754
Not worth the effort.

25:48.892 --> 25:52.067
They’ll go
after the more, uh...

25:52.205 --> 25:54.035
Viking-like teens instead.

25:54.173 --> 25:55.761
[dragons snarling, hissing]

25:55.899 --> 25:58.418
Behind these doors are just
a few of the many species

25:58.557 --> 25:59.765
you will learn to fight.

25:59.903 --> 26:02.215
- The Deadly Nadder.
- [dragon snarls]

26:02.353 --> 26:03.976
Attack eight, armor 16.

26:04.114 --> 26:05.115
GOBBER:
The Hideous Zippleback.

26:05.253 --> 26:06.357
Plus 11 stealth, times two.

26:06.495 --> 26:07.945
The Monstrous Nightmare.

26:08.083 --> 26:09.878
- Firepower 15.
- GOBBER: The Terrible Terror.

26:10.016 --> 26:12.122
- Attack eight, venom 12!
- Will you stop that!

26:13.433 --> 26:15.090
You big bag of wool.

26:17.403 --> 26:20.268
And finally,
the gruesome Gronckle.

26:20.406 --> 26:22.408
[quietly]:
Jaw strength eight.

26:23.478 --> 26:25.445
- [dragon snarling]
- [thumping, chain rattling]

26:25.584 --> 26:27.965
Uh, hey, big guy,
aren’t you gonna, like,

26:28.103 --> 26:29.864
teach us something first?

26:30.002 --> 26:32.936
I believe in learning
on the job.

26:34.454 --> 26:36.146
[snarling]

26:36.284 --> 26:38.562
Today is all about defense.

26:38.700 --> 26:39.977
[snarling]

26:40.115 --> 26:41.669
If you get blasted, you’re out.

26:41.807 --> 26:43.429
Or, you know, dead.

26:43.567 --> 26:45.086
So what’s the first thing
you’re gonna need?

26:45.224 --> 26:46.846
- A shield!
- GOBBER: Shield, yes. Go.

26:46.984 --> 26:48.537
- TUFFNUT: Out of my way.
- RUFFNUT: That one’s mine!

26:48.676 --> 26:51.610
Shield is your most important
piece of equipment.

26:52.956 --> 26:56.097
If you have to choose between
a weapon and a shield...

26:56.960 --> 26:58.340
Just put it down.

26:58.478 --> 26:59.997
Take the shield.

27:00.135 --> 27:01.033
- RUFFNUT: Give it!
- TUFFNUT: Mine, mine, mine!

27:01.171 --> 27:02.275
Find your own shield!

27:02.413 --> 27:03.794
[grunting]

27:05.002 --> 27:06.417
[both yelp]

27:06.555 --> 27:09.489
GOBBER:
Ruffnut, Tuffnut, you’re out.

27:10.318 --> 27:13.355
Shields are good
for another thing: noise.

27:13.493 --> 27:16.151
Make plenty of it
to throw off the dragon’s aim.

27:16.289 --> 27:17.808
[clanging]

27:18.671 --> 27:22.261
Remember, all dragons have
a limited number of blasts.

27:22.399 --> 27:24.090
How many does a Gronckle have?

27:24.228 --> 27:25.713
Ooh, ooh! Six!

27:25.851 --> 27:27.162
Six, yes.

27:27.300 --> 27:28.681
That’s one for each of you.

27:28.819 --> 27:30.579
FISHLEGS:
Although, interesting tidbit,

27:30.718 --> 27:33.410
rocks from different regions
vary in mineral comp...

27:36.827 --> 27:38.518
What are you do...
What are you doing?

27:38.657 --> 27:40.969
What are you doing?
Get in there!

27:42.177 --> 27:43.903
Fishlegs, you’re out.

27:45.042 --> 27:46.734
- ASTRID: Four shots left.
- SNOTLOUT: Yeah.

27:46.872 --> 27:48.736
We’re pretty much gonna be
the stars of this thing.

27:48.874 --> 27:50.392
Almost like we were meant
to be together.

27:50.530 --> 27:52.015
It’s an elimination game,
genius.

27:52.153 --> 27:54.086
There’s only one Top Slayer.

27:55.156 --> 27:57.330
- [whooshing]
- [yelps]

27:57.468 --> 27:59.505
GOBBER:
Snotlout, you’re done. [laughs]

27:59.643 --> 28:01.024
Three shots.

28:01.162 --> 28:03.267
Looks like it’s just
you and me, huh?

28:03.405 --> 28:05.269
Nope. Just me.

28:06.098 --> 28:08.169
Hey! Eyes on me!

28:13.312 --> 28:14.485
[yells]

28:15.314 --> 28:17.765
GOBBER:
Yes. Well done, Astrid.

28:17.903 --> 28:20.250
Two shots left.

28:20.388 --> 28:21.769
Oh, come on.

28:23.356 --> 28:25.427
- Hiccup, you’re out.
- [whimpering]

28:25.565 --> 28:26.705
- One shot left.
- RUFFNUT: Hey, watch it!

28:26.843 --> 28:28.603
[gasping, whimpering]

28:28.741 --> 28:30.847
GOBBER:
Hiccup!

28:32.987 --> 28:35.299
[grunts] End of lesson.

28:35.437 --> 28:38.578
[straining]

28:39.787 --> 28:42.617
Back to bed,
you overgrown sausage.

28:44.688 --> 28:46.897
[dragon grumbling]

28:49.348 --> 28:55.319
Remember, a dragon
will always, always...

28:56.700 --> 28:58.909
...go for the kill.

29:01.843 --> 29:03.707
[sizzling]

29:03.845 --> 29:05.985
♪ ♪

29:08.125 --> 29:09.506
[sighs]

29:12.923 --> 29:15.029
So, why didn’t you?

29:23.831 --> 29:26.178
[birds squawking]

29:31.908 --> 29:34.082
♪ ♪

29:43.298 --> 29:46.060
[birds chirping]

30:01.144 --> 30:03.836
- [dragon roaring]
- [gasping]

30:08.047 --> 30:11.292
[pained shrieking]

30:20.819 --> 30:22.475
Okay.

30:24.477 --> 30:27.687
[squeals, groans]

30:29.137 --> 30:31.726
[dragon moaning softly]

30:46.775 --> 30:50.331
[dragon groaning]

30:52.816 --> 30:54.991
♪ ♪

31:02.308 --> 31:04.483
[groans]

31:06.968 --> 31:08.556
[grunts]

31:13.941 --> 31:15.494
Huh.

31:15.632 --> 31:17.772
- [Hiccup gasps]
- [rattling]

31:22.673 --> 31:24.883
[growls softly]

31:26.229 --> 31:28.438
[thunder rumbling]

31:31.441 --> 31:33.339
GOBBER:
Let’s review, shall we?

31:33.477 --> 31:35.859
Where did Astrid go wrong
in the ring today?

31:35.997 --> 31:37.481
ASTRID:
I mistimed my somersault dive.

31:37.619 --> 31:39.311
It was sloppy.
It threw off my reverse tumble.

31:39.449 --> 31:41.416
- Uh, yeah. We noticed.
- Hey.

31:41.554 --> 31:43.936
Back off my girl. All right?

31:44.074 --> 31:45.593
- She’s trying her best.
- SNOTLOUT: Yeah.

31:45.731 --> 31:47.629
Don’t beat yourself up.
You’ll get it.

31:47.767 --> 31:49.459
Just follow my lead next time.
[pained yell]

31:49.597 --> 31:51.461
GOBBER:
Astrid’s right.

31:51.599 --> 31:53.566
You’ve got to be tough
on yourselves.

31:53.704 --> 31:56.052
All it takes is one weak link.

31:57.570 --> 32:00.090
You made it, then?

32:01.436 --> 32:03.818
You got to start
taking this seriously,

32:03.956 --> 32:05.820
because we are living
in a battleground.

32:05.958 --> 32:08.961
And in case
you haven’t noticed, the other side is winning.

32:09.099 --> 32:11.239
You’re gonna need
every advantage you can get.

32:11.377 --> 32:13.932
So, if you haven’t done
your homework,

32:14.070 --> 32:15.830
allow me to present to you...

32:15.968 --> 32:18.453
♪ ♪

32:20.939 --> 32:22.561
...the Book of Dragons.

32:24.114 --> 32:27.014
Everything we know
about every dragon we know of.

32:27.842 --> 32:29.948
Each of your tribes
brought their wisdom

32:30.086 --> 32:32.191
and experience to these pages.

32:33.503 --> 32:35.470
It’s our most hallowed
possession.

32:35.608 --> 32:37.852
[thunder crashes]

32:37.990 --> 32:40.959
No dragon raids tonight,
so study up.

32:41.097 --> 32:42.408
[Tuffnut stammering]

32:42.546 --> 32:43.892
You mean read?

32:44.031 --> 32:45.929
I’ve read it
like a hundred times.

32:46.067 --> 32:48.311
There’s a Scauldron that sprays
your face with boiling water.

32:48.449 --> 32:51.141
And then there’s,
um, another...

32:51.279 --> 32:53.074
Why would I read words

32:53.212 --> 32:56.181
when I can just kill the stuff
the words tell me stuff about?

32:56.319 --> 32:57.803
Right? I mean, like,
I’m the kind of guy

32:57.941 --> 32:59.770
that other guys
write word books about.

32:59.908 --> 33:01.772
SNOTLOUT [chuckling]:
Nice.

33:01.910 --> 33:03.602
- SNOTLOUT and TUFFNUT: Boys!
- FISHLEGS: Don’t worry, though.

33:03.740 --> 33:06.156
I’m here for all of your
dragon-related inquiries, okay?

33:06.294 --> 33:07.468
Theories, stats.

33:07.606 --> 33:10.781
I’ve even made,
um, cards, um...

33:12.093 --> 33:13.474
You can ask me anything.

33:13.612 --> 33:14.509
- RUFFNUT: Stop following me.
- FISHLEGS: Here.

33:14.647 --> 33:15.579
How about now? Try me now.

33:15.717 --> 33:17.685
RUFFNUT:
Absolutely not.

33:25.451 --> 33:27.039
So...

33:27.177 --> 33:30.422
sounds like a gruesome,
grisly, good time, huh?

33:31.354 --> 33:32.458
Read it.

33:32.596 --> 33:34.460
Y-You know, uh...

33:34.598 --> 33:37.049
maybe they’re not as bad
as we think they are.

33:39.534 --> 33:41.847
Are you actually insane,
or do you just act that way?

33:41.985 --> 33:44.401
Is-is there...
is there a third option?

33:45.885 --> 33:47.991
Wiping out dragons
is why we’re here.

33:48.129 --> 33:50.787
It’s why the best
of our tribes came together.

33:50.925 --> 33:54.032
Because yes, dragons are
as bad as we think.

33:54.170 --> 33:55.930
Y-Yeah, I-I know.
I’m just saying,

33:56.068 --> 33:57.759
maybe we’re part
of the problem.

33:57.897 --> 34:01.798
You know, moving in on
their lands, eating their food.

34:06.596 --> 34:08.149
Wow.

34:08.287 --> 34:10.255
You live in
a different world, don’t you?

34:10.393 --> 34:11.773
What?

34:11.911 --> 34:14.224
Just coast by,
taking it all for granted.

34:14.362 --> 34:15.605
Well, I don’t think that...

34:15.743 --> 34:16.813
Never having to work
for anything,

34:16.951 --> 34:18.159
never struggling
to get a foot up.

34:18.297 --> 34:20.161
Well, guess what.

34:20.299 --> 34:22.163
I come from nothing.

34:22.301 --> 34:26.409
No chief for a dad,
no handouts, no excuses.

34:26.547 --> 34:28.342
I’m not afraid of hard work.

34:28.480 --> 34:29.998
I’m willing to do whatever
it takes to get the job done,

34:30.137 --> 34:31.759
which, in this case,
means wiping out the dragons

34:31.897 --> 34:33.588
for the good of everyone.

34:34.520 --> 34:35.797
Yeah.

34:36.695 --> 34:37.903
You know what else?

34:38.041 --> 34:40.768
I’m-I’m afraid...
afraid to ask.

34:43.150 --> 34:46.498
I’ve got my eye
on that big house of yours.

34:46.636 --> 34:48.741
I’m gonna be chief one day.

34:49.949 --> 34:51.813
I-I don’t doubt it.

34:52.780 --> 34:55.265
Actually, I think
my dad would be thrilled.

34:55.403 --> 34:57.509
Besides, you’re the kid
he always hoped for.

34:57.647 --> 35:00.028
Instead, he got...

35:00.167 --> 35:01.685
all this.

35:03.756 --> 35:05.827
Stay out of my way, Hiccup.

35:09.969 --> 35:12.144
♪ ♪

35:12.282 --> 35:13.732
[sighs]

35:13.870 --> 35:16.735
[thunder crashes]

35:21.533 --> 35:23.397
"Dragon classifications.

35:23.535 --> 35:27.021
"Strike class. Fear class.
Mystery class.

35:29.610 --> 35:31.405
"Thunderdrum.

35:31.543 --> 35:33.579
"When startled, the Thunderdrum
produces a concussive sound

35:33.717 --> 35:35.616
"that can kill a man
at close range.

35:35.754 --> 35:37.756
"Extremely dangerous.
Kill on sight.

35:37.894 --> 35:39.723
"Timberjack.

35:39.861 --> 35:41.725
"Skrill. Whispering Death.

35:41.863 --> 35:43.969
"Burns its victims.
Buries its victims.

35:44.107 --> 35:46.661
"Chokes its victims.
Turns its victims inside out.

35:46.799 --> 35:49.043
"Extremely dangerous.
Extremely dangerous.

35:49.181 --> 35:52.150
"Kill on sight. Kill on sight.
Kill on sight.

35:53.530 --> 35:55.532
"Night Fury.

35:56.499 --> 35:58.915
"Size: unknown. Speed: unknown.

35:59.053 --> 36:01.814
"The unholy offspring
of lightning and death itself.

36:01.952 --> 36:05.024
Never engage this dragon."

36:16.277 --> 36:19.177
STOICK:
I can almost smell them.

36:27.357 --> 36:31.706
Take us in to Helheim’s Gate.

36:31.844 --> 36:33.743
Here we go again.

36:33.881 --> 36:36.194
Hard to port!

36:37.919 --> 36:40.198
SPITELOUT:
Hard to port!

36:42.545 --> 36:45.893
- Set the oars! Furl the sails!
- [others chattering]

36:46.031 --> 36:47.377
All together.

36:47.515 --> 36:48.999
Come on.

36:49.137 --> 36:50.829
Higher.

36:52.589 --> 36:54.557
[chatter continues
indistinctly]

36:54.695 --> 36:56.869
♪ ♪

37:17.165 --> 37:19.927
[rocks clattering]

37:20.065 --> 37:22.274
[ship scraping along rocks]

37:38.048 --> 37:39.153
We’re not alone!

37:39.291 --> 37:40.775
- Look up!
- Watch your heads!

37:40.913 --> 37:41.949
[dragon snarling]

37:42.087 --> 37:45.159
[frantic chatter]

37:49.025 --> 37:50.613
[screaming]

37:51.752 --> 37:54.306
[frantic chatter continues]

37:56.446 --> 37:58.172
Turn back!

37:58.310 --> 38:01.348
- PHLEGMA: They’re everywhere!
- [screeching]

38:02.763 --> 38:05.731
Hey, I just, uh...
I just happened to notice

38:05.869 --> 38:08.803
that the book had nothing
on Night Furies.

38:08.941 --> 38:11.772
Is there maybe, like,
like, another book?

38:11.910 --> 38:13.256
Maybe, like,
a Night Fury pamph...

38:13.394 --> 38:14.982
[screeching, snarling]

38:15.120 --> 38:16.501
GOBBER:
Focus, Hiccup.

38:16.639 --> 38:18.641
You’re not even trying.

38:19.469 --> 38:21.506
Today is about attack.

38:21.644 --> 38:24.060
Nadders are quick
and light on their feet.

38:24.198 --> 38:27.650
Your job is to be quicker
and lighter.

38:27.788 --> 38:30.066
[panting]

38:33.276 --> 38:34.898
- [gasps]
- [snarls, shrieks]

38:35.036 --> 38:37.315
- [grunts]
- Sorry. [whimpers]

38:39.524 --> 38:43.182
I’m really beginning to
question your teaching methods!

38:43.321 --> 38:44.632
GOBBER:
Look for its blind spot.

38:44.770 --> 38:45.978
Every dragon has one.

38:46.116 --> 38:49.672
Find it, hide in it,
then strike.

38:52.191 --> 38:53.883
[groans] Do you ever bathe?

38:54.021 --> 38:57.162
If you don’t like it, go find
your own blind spot. Go!

38:57.990 --> 38:59.509
- [whimpering]
- GOBBER: Blind spot, yes.

38:59.647 --> 39:01.269
Deaf spot, not so much.

39:01.408 --> 39:02.719
[laughs]

39:02.857 --> 39:04.894
TUFFNUT:
I am hurt. I am very much hurt.

39:05.032 --> 39:07.448
So, how does one sneak up
on a Night Fury?

39:07.586 --> 39:10.106
No one has ever met one
and lived to tell the tale.

39:10.244 --> 39:11.901
- Now, get in there!
- Yeah, I-I know.

39:12.039 --> 39:13.109
I-I’m just saying, like,

39:13.247 --> 39:15.422
- how would...
- ASTRID: Hiccup.

39:15.560 --> 39:17.044
Down.

39:20.012 --> 39:22.221
[panting quietly]

39:23.913 --> 39:25.880
[dragon growling softly]

39:27.399 --> 39:28.952
[snarling]

39:29.781 --> 39:31.886
- SNOTLOUT: Whoa, save yourself!
- [Astrid grunts]

39:32.024 --> 39:33.129
I’ll take care of this.

39:33.267 --> 39:35.062
[grunting]

39:35.200 --> 39:36.443
Oh.

39:37.271 --> 39:38.617
Not my fault, Astrid.

39:38.755 --> 39:41.448
I got distracted
by the light in your eyes.

39:43.208 --> 39:45.590
[dragon snarling]

39:45.728 --> 39:48.558
[dragon shrieking, roaring]

40:03.470 --> 40:04.919
[pained shrieking]

40:10.477 --> 40:13.928
- [grunting]
- HICCUP: Wait! Just let me...

40:16.344 --> 40:17.932
[grunts fiercely]

40:21.936 --> 40:24.629
[dragon shrieking]

40:25.423 --> 40:27.873
- [Astrid grunting]
- [dragon whimpers]

40:30.255 --> 40:31.981
Yes. Well done, Astrid.

40:32.119 --> 40:33.327
Nothing like giving them

40:33.465 --> 40:34.673
a taste of
their own medicine, eh?

40:34.811 --> 40:37.504
Also, "Well done, Snotlout,

40:37.642 --> 40:39.298
with the assist," right?
What a team!

40:39.437 --> 40:41.853
Is anyone taking this
seriously?!

40:41.991 --> 40:43.544
Take it seriously.

40:43.682 --> 40:45.166
’Cause in case you forgot,
our parents’ war

40:45.304 --> 40:46.927
is about to become ours!

40:51.828 --> 40:53.934
Figure out
which side you’re on.

40:54.762 --> 40:56.937
♪ ♪

41:04.634 --> 41:06.843
[grunting, panting]

41:08.500 --> 41:11.020
[distant birdcalls]

41:16.301 --> 41:18.476
♪ ♪

41:31.592 --> 41:33.180
[sighs]

41:36.908 --> 41:38.772
[gasping breaths]

41:38.910 --> 41:41.153
[growling softly]

41:43.190 --> 41:44.881
Hmm? Huh?

41:45.019 --> 41:46.365
[sniffing]

41:49.265 --> 41:51.060
[growls softly]

41:57.135 --> 41:59.137
[dragon snarls]

42:01.898 --> 42:03.969
[knife splashes in water]

42:06.109 --> 42:07.386
[exhales sharply]

42:10.597 --> 42:12.288
[sniffing softly]

42:16.223 --> 42:19.053
Huh. Toothless.

42:20.089 --> 42:22.056
I could’ve sworn you had...

42:24.472 --> 42:25.888
...teeth.

42:27.993 --> 42:30.099
[growling softly]

42:30.237 --> 42:32.446
[stammering]:
I don’t have any more.

42:32.584 --> 42:35.035
[Hiccup panting]

42:35.173 --> 42:36.726
[Toothless moans softly]

42:36.864 --> 42:39.142
[Toothless retching]

42:42.111 --> 42:43.457
[groans]

42:52.086 --> 42:54.054
[Toothless moans gently]

42:54.192 --> 42:55.573
Thanks?

42:57.057 --> 42:59.956
[moans, grunts]

43:01.544 --> 43:03.028
[whimpers]

43:03.926 --> 43:06.100
Oh, come on.
You’re kidding, right?

43:07.032 --> 43:08.413
[purrs]

43:08.551 --> 43:10.449
[sighs]

43:11.381 --> 43:13.936
[takes deep breath]

43:17.387 --> 43:18.906
[grunts]

43:20.252 --> 43:21.633
Mmm.

43:22.461 --> 43:24.774
- Hmm?
- [Toothless moans softly]

43:25.913 --> 43:27.156
[whimpers]

43:29.468 --> 43:30.953
[groans]

43:31.091 --> 43:33.990
- [Toothless grunts]
- [sighs]

43:35.613 --> 43:37.615
[gagging]

43:41.998 --> 43:43.551
[grunts]

43:43.690 --> 43:45.036
[sighs]

43:45.174 --> 43:47.452
[chuckles, sighs]

43:47.590 --> 43:50.213
[chittering]

43:59.982 --> 44:02.432
[growling]

44:18.310 --> 44:20.071
[moans softly]

44:21.624 --> 44:23.591
[moans]

44:29.183 --> 44:31.496
- [growls]
- [Hiccup gasps]

44:31.634 --> 44:33.636
[moans]

44:33.774 --> 44:35.949
♪ ♪

44:39.642 --> 44:41.092
[moans softly]

44:51.999 --> 44:54.692
[Toothless breathing heavily]

44:58.212 --> 45:00.663
[Toothless moaning curiously]

45:09.534 --> 45:11.225
[branch snaps]

45:11.363 --> 45:13.434
[dragging]

45:25.723 --> 45:27.897
[Toothless moaning]

45:45.121 --> 45:46.226
[moans]

45:46.364 --> 45:48.573
♪ ♪

45:56.892 --> 45:58.272
[growls]

46:01.413 --> 46:02.932
[moans]

46:05.521 --> 46:06.936
[growls, moans]

46:07.074 --> 46:08.041
[growls]

46:08.179 --> 46:09.283
[moans]

46:09.421 --> 46:11.389
♪ ♪

46:22.607 --> 46:25.817
[Toothless grunting]

46:30.718 --> 46:34.308
[moans, growls]

46:36.000 --> 46:38.174
♪ ♪

46:54.018 --> 46:56.123
[moans softly]

46:59.851 --> 47:01.646
[exhales sharply]

47:04.166 --> 47:06.375
GOBBER: <i>And then</i>
<i>he turned and grabbed me arm,</i>

47:06.513 --> 47:08.411
and with one twist,

47:08.549 --> 47:11.829
he took my hand clean off
and he swallowed it whole.

47:11.967 --> 47:13.831
Yeah, he must have spread
the word around,

47:13.969 --> 47:17.179
’cause within a month,
another one had taken my leg.

47:17.317 --> 47:18.594
FISHLEGS:
Probably a Skrill.

47:18.732 --> 47:21.424
Serrated teeth,
jaw strength 17.

47:21.562 --> 47:23.841
SNOTLOUT: I’ll avenge
your fallen limbs, big guy.

47:23.979 --> 47:25.394
I’ll chop off
the hands and feet

47:25.532 --> 47:27.914
- of every dragon that I see.
- GOBBER: Nah.

47:29.708 --> 47:31.469
It’s the wings
and the tail you want.

47:31.607 --> 47:34.437
If they can’t fly,
they can’t get away.

47:34.575 --> 47:37.233
A downed dragon
is a dead dragon.

47:37.371 --> 47:40.202
Anyone can get by
without the other bits.

47:40.340 --> 47:41.893
SNOTLOUT:
I’m gonna lose all of my limbs.

47:42.031 --> 47:44.827
I volunteer Ruffnut
to lose at least one limb.

47:44.965 --> 47:45.897
Huh?

47:46.035 --> 47:47.416
TUFFNUT:
What?

47:47.554 --> 47:48.589
We’re twins.
Your pain is my pain.

47:48.727 --> 47:50.212
GOBBER:
You’re twins?

47:50.350 --> 47:52.386
Even our own mother
can’t tell us apart.

47:52.524 --> 47:54.423
It’s uncanny.

47:54.561 --> 47:55.700
There we go.

47:55.838 --> 47:57.736
Astrid’s got the right idea.

47:57.875 --> 47:59.946
Get your sleep while you can.

48:00.808 --> 48:02.465
Soon, Stoick will be back.

48:02.603 --> 48:05.365
And one of you will be chosen
to kill the dragon.

48:05.503 --> 48:08.506
Question is: Who?

48:08.644 --> 48:10.094
[grunts]

48:10.232 --> 48:12.372
[air pumping]

48:12.510 --> 48:14.719
♪ ♪

48:37.915 --> 48:40.089
♪ ♪

48:49.236 --> 48:50.513
Toothless!

48:50.651 --> 48:52.032
- [Toothless moans]
- [panting]

48:52.170 --> 48:53.620
Brought breakfast.

48:57.589 --> 49:00.144
[grunts, panting]

49:00.282 --> 49:03.354
- Huh? What do you think, bud?
- [sniffing]

49:03.492 --> 49:04.976
Okay.

49:06.219 --> 49:08.669
We got some cod...

49:09.532 --> 49:11.086
...some salmon

49:11.224 --> 49:13.019
and a whole smoked eel.

49:13.157 --> 49:15.745
- [distressed moaning]
- Whoa, uh, uh, uh...

49:15.883 --> 49:17.851
No eel! Scratch the eel!

49:17.989 --> 49:19.853
[panting]

49:19.991 --> 49:23.339
Yeah, I, uh,
can’t say I love it, either.

49:23.477 --> 49:25.824
[Toothless moaning gently]

49:28.689 --> 49:29.794
That’s it.

49:29.932 --> 49:31.899
Stick to the good stuff.

49:32.038 --> 49:36.387
I’ll just be back here,

49:36.525 --> 49:38.976
minding my own business.

49:41.909 --> 49:43.428
Okay.

49:50.435 --> 49:52.990
[grunting]

50:02.171 --> 50:05.071
Okay. Okay.

50:06.348 --> 50:08.522
[moaning]

50:08.660 --> 50:11.422
Whew. Okay. Not bad.

50:11.560 --> 50:12.664
It could work.

50:12.802 --> 50:14.390
If it’s... Whoa! Okay!

50:14.528 --> 50:17.014
Toothless, no! Oh, gods!

50:17.980 --> 50:19.913
[Hiccup screaming]

50:20.051 --> 50:21.018
Toothless!

50:21.156 --> 50:21.984
Oh, gods!

50:22.122 --> 50:24.090
[screaming]

50:24.228 --> 50:25.298
[roars]

50:25.436 --> 50:27.886
[frightened yelling, gasping]

50:32.857 --> 50:34.962
[gasps] It’s working!

50:35.101 --> 50:37.758
[laughing]:
Yeah! Whoo!

50:37.896 --> 50:39.243
[yelps]

50:39.381 --> 50:41.210
[squeals]

50:44.317 --> 50:47.389
Yeah! Whoo!

50:47.527 --> 50:49.736
GOBBER:
<i>Today is all about teamwork.</i>

50:49.874 --> 50:54.085
If you work together,
you might just survive.

50:55.259 --> 50:59.401
You see, a wet dragon head
cannot light its fire.

50:59.539 --> 51:02.093
But a Hideous Zippleback
is extra tricky,

51:02.231 --> 51:05.269
’cause one head breathes gas
and the other head lights it.

51:05.407 --> 51:08.893
Your job is to know
which is which.

51:09.031 --> 51:10.136
Good luck.

51:10.274 --> 51:13.277
[dragon snarling quietly]

51:13.415 --> 51:17.729
Razor-sharp fangs that inject
venom for predigestion.

51:17.867 --> 51:20.629
- Prefers to keep its victims...
- Shh!

51:20.767 --> 51:22.251
[whispers]:
...conscious.

51:22.389 --> 51:25.082
You know, I’m kind of glad
we got partnered.

51:25.979 --> 51:28.637
Us girls got to stick together.

51:28.775 --> 51:30.673
- Until I have to take you out.
- Shush.

51:30.811 --> 51:32.710
SNOTLOUT: I think I’ve
pretty much won Astrid over.

51:32.848 --> 51:34.367
I mean, she can barely even
look at me.

51:34.505 --> 51:37.232
[chuckles] You came
to the right man for advice.

51:37.370 --> 51:38.992
- I didn’t ask...
- If there’s one thing

51:39.130 --> 51:41.443
the Viking girl brain
can’t resist, it’s...

51:41.581 --> 51:42.961
- [dragon chittering]
- SNOTLOUT: Look out!

51:43.100 --> 51:44.653
[Tuffnut gasps]

51:44.791 --> 51:47.138
- ASTRID: Hey!
- RUFFNUT: It’s us, geniuses.

51:47.276 --> 51:48.346
TUFFNUT:
Lightning reflexes.

51:48.484 --> 51:49.899
I see hideous heads, I strike.

51:50.037 --> 51:51.798
- [grunts]
- Ow.

51:51.936 --> 51:53.248
[chuckles] Whoa.

51:53.386 --> 51:55.008
Uh, make that
one hideous head, Astrid.

51:55.146 --> 51:56.147
[dragon growls]

51:56.285 --> 51:57.942
[all grunting]

51:58.080 --> 51:59.185
[Tuffnut panting rapidly]

51:59.323 --> 52:01.428
TUFFNUT:
Save yourselves!

52:02.188 --> 52:04.328
Also known
to toy with its victims,

52:04.466 --> 52:06.123
dismembering them
limb from limb.

52:06.261 --> 52:08.711
Will you please stop that?

52:10.817 --> 52:12.059
Fishlegs!

52:14.786 --> 52:16.340
FISHLEGS:
Wrong head.

52:16.478 --> 52:18.169
[Fishlegs whimpers]

52:19.929 --> 52:21.483
Get out of there, Hiccup!

52:21.621 --> 52:22.967
[grunts]

52:23.105 --> 52:24.658
Oh, come on. [grunting]

52:24.796 --> 52:27.834
- [dragon hissing]
- [Hiccup gasping]

52:28.800 --> 52:30.008
[sparks crackling]

52:30.147 --> 52:31.182
[sniffs]

52:31.320 --> 52:33.529
[moaning]

52:34.806 --> 52:37.015
Yeah. Back!

52:37.154 --> 52:38.258
[grunts]

52:38.396 --> 52:41.088
Run... Hiccup.

52:41.227 --> 52:43.436
HICCUP: Don’t make me
tell you again! Yeah.

52:43.574 --> 52:45.886
Yeah, that’s right.
Back in your pen.

52:46.024 --> 52:48.337
[snarling]

52:49.200 --> 52:51.409
Now, think about
what you’ve done.

52:51.547 --> 52:52.962
[hisses viciously]

52:53.100 --> 52:54.688
[whimpers]

53:09.910 --> 53:12.534
So, are we done today?

53:12.672 --> 53:15.744
J-Just because I have
some things I need to, uh...

53:16.710 --> 53:19.161
Yeah, I’m gonna... I’m gonna
see you guys tomorrow.

53:19.299 --> 53:21.370
♪ ♪

53:21.508 --> 53:22.889
[chuckles]

53:26.893 --> 53:27.756
Huh?

53:27.894 --> 53:29.413
[chittering]

53:29.551 --> 53:30.759
Hey.

53:30.897 --> 53:32.243
Oh, come on.

53:32.381 --> 53:33.693
Just try it.

53:38.076 --> 53:40.251
♪ ♪

53:43.772 --> 53:45.601
Whoa!

53:45.739 --> 53:47.431
Oh, I’m gonna die!

53:48.604 --> 53:50.434
Whoa, whoa, no!

53:52.263 --> 53:53.299
No, please!

53:53.437 --> 53:56.474
Just kind of angle yourself.

53:56.612 --> 53:58.683
Whoa!

54:02.031 --> 54:04.241
Whoa, whoa, no! [yells]

54:06.277 --> 54:08.314
[screams]:
Oh, come on!

54:08.452 --> 54:09.763
[grunts]

54:09.901 --> 54:12.249
[panting]

54:12.387 --> 54:15.735
[sneezing]

54:20.291 --> 54:22.604
[continues sneezing]

54:23.743 --> 54:25.434
- RUFFNUT: Out of my way.
- TUFFNUT: Move!

54:25.572 --> 54:27.022
Move, move, move,
move, move, move!

54:27.160 --> 54:28.989
ASTRID: Watch yourselves.
Get in its blind spot.

54:29.127 --> 54:30.508
SNOTLOUT:
I got it! It’s mine!

54:30.646 --> 54:32.130
ASTRID:
No, don’t bring it over here!

54:32.269 --> 54:34.443
[Tuffnut whimpers, grunts]

54:36.790 --> 54:38.827
[sneezing]

54:44.936 --> 54:46.973
TUFFNUT: Uh, little guy.
What is his name again?

54:47.111 --> 54:49.251
- RUFFNUT: I don’t remember.
- TUFFNUT: Hey. Slow down.

54:49.389 --> 54:51.184
- Are you trying to show us up?
- N-No.

54:51.322 --> 54:52.944
I’ve never seen someone
take down a Gronckle like that.

54:53.082 --> 54:54.774
I mean, I do it all the time,
but how did you learn?

54:54.912 --> 54:56.983
Learn what?
What exactly was that?

54:57.121 --> 54:59.123
Okay, see,
I-I’d love to explain.

54:59.261 --> 55:01.712
It’s just, I left my axe
back in-in the ring.

55:01.850 --> 55:03.507
Who’s a good boy?
Who’s a good boy?

55:03.645 --> 55:05.474
Whoa, okay. [laughs]

55:05.612 --> 55:07.752
Yeah, yeah? You itchy?

55:07.890 --> 55:09.340
Is that the spot?

55:09.478 --> 55:11.653
[Toothless purring]

55:13.482 --> 55:16.174
[moaning gently]

55:18.487 --> 55:19.971
[grunts]

55:25.494 --> 55:26.978
[shrieks]

55:31.638 --> 55:33.951
[dragon grunting]

55:37.748 --> 55:38.818
[yells]

55:40.509 --> 55:42.511
[moaning softly]

55:43.995 --> 55:45.652
Hiccup.

55:47.033 --> 55:48.897
♪ ♪

55:49.035 --> 55:50.657
SNOTLOUT:
Yo, there he is.

55:50.795 --> 55:52.659
Hey, Hiccup. [grunts]

55:52.797 --> 55:54.385
- Okay.
- Hiccup. W-W-Wait.

55:54.523 --> 55:56.249
- I have a proper question.
- So I’m thinking that...

55:56.387 --> 55:58.527
SNOTLOUT: All it needs to be
is you and me in the ring.

55:58.665 --> 56:00.840
♪ ♪

56:07.225 --> 56:09.089
A Terrible Terror! [grunts]

56:09.227 --> 56:11.402
♪ ♪

56:15.199 --> 56:16.649
[chittering]

56:16.787 --> 56:18.409
[chuckles]
It’s like the size of my...

56:18.547 --> 56:19.479
[grunts]

56:19.617 --> 56:20.894
[groans] Get it off!

56:21.032 --> 56:22.724
Get it off! Get it off!

56:24.208 --> 56:27.556
[snarling]

56:41.708 --> 56:44.711
[lively chatter]

56:45.816 --> 56:47.645
[grunting fiercely]

56:56.102 --> 56:57.483
[grunts]

56:57.621 --> 57:00.037
♪ ♪

57:20.471 --> 57:22.818
♪ ♪

57:22.956 --> 57:25.234
[wind whistling]

57:25.372 --> 57:27.167
[Toothless moans]

57:30.136 --> 57:32.345
[moaning gently]

57:41.285 --> 57:42.562
[squeals]

57:42.700 --> 57:44.012
[Hiccup grunts]

57:44.978 --> 57:47.533
[grunting]

57:48.430 --> 57:49.845
[Toothless moans gently]

57:49.983 --> 57:51.640
HICCUP:
Ow.

57:52.469 --> 57:55.472
[birds screeching]

57:55.610 --> 57:57.474
♪ ♪

57:57.612 --> 57:59.786
[quiet chatter]

58:06.413 --> 58:08.277
And the other ships?

58:10.521 --> 58:12.799
[groaning]

58:20.358 --> 58:21.912
Dad!

58:22.050 --> 58:23.016
I got it.

58:23.154 --> 58:24.362
[grunts]

58:24.501 --> 58:25.605
I missed you.

58:25.743 --> 58:27.676
In, like, a super manly way.

58:27.814 --> 58:30.161
I got so much to tell you
about the Trial of Flame.

58:30.299 --> 58:32.612
It’s basically between... Dad?

58:33.855 --> 58:35.235
Dad?

58:36.443 --> 58:37.479
Da...

58:37.617 --> 58:39.377
Okay, I’ll see you at home.

58:39.516 --> 58:41.725
GOBBER:
So, no nest, then?

58:41.863 --> 58:44.279
Not even close.

58:44.417 --> 58:46.350
I hope you had more success.

58:46.488 --> 58:47.903
Well, if by success,

58:48.041 --> 58:49.629
you mean your parenting
troubles are over,

58:49.767 --> 58:51.942
then, uh, yeah.

58:52.080 --> 58:53.391
[laughter]

58:53.530 --> 58:55.117
Did you hear the news, Chief?
[laughs]

58:55.255 --> 58:57.948
- Everyone is so relieved.
- Good riddance to old Hiccup.

58:58.086 --> 58:59.536
SNORTI [chuckles]:
Aye.

58:59.674 --> 59:01.641
No one will miss that nuisance.

59:03.919 --> 59:06.266
Hiccup is...

59:06.404 --> 59:07.509
gone?

59:07.647 --> 59:09.097
Yeah.

59:09.235 --> 59:11.375
Yeah, most afternoons,
but who can blame him?

59:11.513 --> 59:13.342
The life of a celebrity
can be very rough.

59:13.480 --> 59:14.930
He can barely walk
through the village

59:15.068 --> 59:17.830
without being swarmed
by his army of new fans.

59:17.968 --> 59:19.314
[Gobber chuckles]

59:19.452 --> 59:21.903
Who would’ve thought
he has this...

59:22.041 --> 59:24.630
way with the beasts?

59:26.908 --> 59:29.082
♪ ♪

59:36.573 --> 59:37.953
All right, bud.

59:38.091 --> 59:40.542
We’re gonna take this
nice and slow.

59:42.233 --> 59:43.718
Here we go.

59:43.856 --> 59:44.926
Position three.

59:45.064 --> 59:46.790
Uh, no, four.

59:55.557 --> 59:57.732
[roars]

01:00:02.633 --> 01:00:04.255
You ready?

01:00:08.639 --> 01:00:11.400
[Toothless roars]

01:00:18.753 --> 01:00:20.617
Come on. Come on.

01:00:20.755 --> 01:00:23.309
[birds screeching]

01:00:26.139 --> 01:00:27.727
[chuckles]

01:00:27.865 --> 01:00:29.764
[moans softly]

01:00:36.460 --> 01:00:38.531
Yeah, look at us!

01:00:38.669 --> 01:00:40.982
[yelps] Whoa!

01:00:41.810 --> 01:00:44.295
- My fault. My fault.
- [Toothless squeals]

01:00:44.433 --> 01:00:46.263
Yeah, yeah, I’m on it.

01:00:46.401 --> 01:00:47.713
Position five.

01:00:50.888 --> 01:00:52.338
Come on, bud.

01:00:56.653 --> 01:00:59.000
Yeah. Go, baby!

01:00:59.138 --> 01:01:01.002
Oh, this is amazing!

01:01:01.140 --> 01:01:02.969
The wind in my...

01:01:03.107 --> 01:01:05.627
Cheat sheet! Stop!

01:01:08.423 --> 01:01:09.735
[whimpering]

01:01:09.873 --> 01:01:12.565
Oh, gods!

01:01:12.703 --> 01:01:14.671
- [screaming]
- [Toothless roars]

01:01:14.809 --> 01:01:17.846
♪ ♪

01:01:28.995 --> 01:01:30.963
[whimpers, grunts]

01:01:31.101 --> 01:01:33.275
[straining]

01:01:35.484 --> 01:01:38.591
- [Toothless roaring]
- [Hiccup yelling]

01:01:40.731 --> 01:01:43.009
[straining]

01:01:44.459 --> 01:01:46.219
[roars]

01:01:49.498 --> 01:01:52.260
[grunting, panting]

01:01:54.020 --> 01:01:55.642
[grunts]

01:01:57.230 --> 01:01:59.129
[Toothless roars]

01:02:03.340 --> 01:02:05.549
♪ ♪

01:02:20.909 --> 01:02:21.979
Yeah!

01:02:22.117 --> 01:02:23.740
[snarls playfully]

01:02:34.060 --> 01:02:34.992
STOICK:
Son!

01:02:35.130 --> 01:02:36.683
Dad! Uh, you’re back.

01:02:36.822 --> 01:02:38.927
Uh, uh, oh...
Okay, uh, Gobber’s not here,

01:02:39.065 --> 01:02:41.067
- so, um...
- I know.

01:02:43.483 --> 01:02:44.968
Came looking for you.

01:02:45.106 --> 01:02:47.487
You-you-you did? Uh, wh-why?

01:02:47.625 --> 01:02:49.489
You’ve been keeping secrets.

01:02:49.627 --> 01:02:51.319
I have?

01:02:51.457 --> 01:02:54.287
Just how long did you think
you could hide it from me?

01:02:55.047 --> 01:02:56.807
I-I don’t even know
what you’re talking...

01:02:56.945 --> 01:03:02.640
Nothing happens on this island
without me hearing about it.

01:03:03.918 --> 01:03:09.233
So, let’s talk
about that dragon.

01:03:09.371 --> 01:03:10.787
Oh, gods, Dad.

01:03:10.925 --> 01:03:12.685
I’m-I’m-I’m so sorry.

01:03:12.823 --> 01:03:14.204
I-I was gonna tell you sooner.

01:03:14.342 --> 01:03:15.964
[stammering]:
I just didn’t know...

01:03:16.102 --> 01:03:18.691
[Stoick laughing]

01:03:18.829 --> 01:03:19.934
[chuckles]

01:03:20.072 --> 01:03:21.349
[continues laughing]

01:03:21.487 --> 01:03:23.730
[chuckles] You’re not upset?

01:03:23.869 --> 01:03:25.905
What? What?

01:03:26.043 --> 01:03:28.045
I was hoping for this.

01:03:28.183 --> 01:03:29.875
- You were?
- [laughing]: Oh, yes.

01:03:30.013 --> 01:03:33.050
And believe me,
it only gets better.

01:03:33.188 --> 01:03:35.225
Just wait till you spill

01:03:35.363 --> 01:03:37.365
a Nadder’s guts
for the first time.

01:03:37.503 --> 01:03:42.473
Or-or mount your first
Gronckle head on a spear.

01:03:42.611 --> 01:03:44.510
What a feeling.

01:03:44.648 --> 01:03:46.823
You really had me
going there, son.

01:03:46.961 --> 01:03:50.654
All those years
of the worst Viking

01:03:50.792 --> 01:03:53.036
Berk has ever seen.

01:03:53.174 --> 01:03:55.038
Odin, it was rough.

01:03:55.176 --> 01:03:56.694
I almost gave up on you.

01:03:56.833 --> 01:03:59.836
And all the while,
you were holding out on me.

01:03:59.974 --> 01:04:01.009
- [groans softly]
- [Stoick laughs]

01:04:01.147 --> 01:04:03.184
Thor almighty.

01:04:03.322 --> 01:04:05.462
Who would have thought
that dragon training

01:04:05.600 --> 01:04:08.568
would have been
your place to shine, huh?

01:04:08.706 --> 01:04:11.640
Ah, you might even win
Top Slayer.

01:04:11.778 --> 01:04:13.159
Just like your old man.

01:04:13.297 --> 01:04:15.161
- Who knows? [chuckles]
- [Stoick laughing]

01:04:15.299 --> 01:04:16.783
You know... [grunts]

01:04:16.922 --> 01:04:18.889
with you doing so well
in the ring...

01:04:19.027 --> 01:04:20.649
I’m gonna... I’m gonna...

01:04:20.787 --> 01:04:22.065
- Sit.
- Okay.

01:04:22.203 --> 01:04:25.206
We finally have something
to talk about.

01:04:25.344 --> 01:04:27.035
[Stoick chuckles]

01:04:32.592 --> 01:04:34.387
So, I...

01:04:40.393 --> 01:04:41.670
[stammers]

01:04:41.808 --> 01:04:43.707
[both chuckle awkwardly]

01:04:44.881 --> 01:04:47.297
Oh! Oh, I, uh...

01:04:47.435 --> 01:04:49.886
I brought you something...
[grunts]

01:04:50.024 --> 01:04:52.371
to... to, uh...

01:04:52.509 --> 01:04:55.684
keep you safe in the ring.

01:04:57.963 --> 01:05:00.897
Your mother would have
wanted you to have it.

01:05:01.725 --> 01:05:03.761
W-Wow. Uh, thanks.

01:05:03.900 --> 01:05:05.660
It’s half of her breastplate.

01:05:05.798 --> 01:05:06.937
[Stoick chuckles]

01:05:07.075 --> 01:05:09.112
Matching set.

01:05:09.250 --> 01:05:11.528
Keeps her...

01:05:11.666 --> 01:05:13.806
It keeps her close, you know?

01:05:15.704 --> 01:05:17.327
Wear it proudly, son.

01:05:17.465 --> 01:05:20.537
You’ve held up
your end of the deal.

01:05:25.266 --> 01:05:26.681
[yawns] Yeah.

01:05:26.819 --> 01:05:29.063
- Yeah. Tired.
- Yeah, I’m gonna...

01:05:29.201 --> 01:05:31.099
- I’m gonna get some s-sleep.
- Uh, good talk.

01:05:31.237 --> 01:05:32.825
- Big day tomorrow.
- Yeah. [stammers]

01:05:32.963 --> 01:05:34.275
The Trial of Flame,
and it takes a lot out of you.

01:05:34.413 --> 01:05:36.001
Yeah, Trial of Flames--
Flame. [chuckles]

01:05:36.139 --> 01:05:37.830
- Good luck with that.
- Yeah, thank you, thank you

01:05:37.968 --> 01:05:38.935
- for the, uh... the breast hat.
- I hope you like the...

01:05:39.073 --> 01:05:41.627
- Hat. Yeah.
- Yeah.

01:05:41.765 --> 01:05:44.733
Okay, well...
[chuckles] good night.

01:05:46.321 --> 01:05:49.462
- [clattering]
- [sighs]

01:05:49.600 --> 01:05:51.809
[chittering]

01:05:53.639 --> 01:05:55.261
No more of your tricks.

01:05:55.399 --> 01:05:57.194
- I’m taking Top Slayer today.
- Yeah, yeah, okay.

01:05:57.332 --> 01:05:59.956
It’s-it’s all yours.
Top-Top Slay away.

01:06:00.094 --> 01:06:01.302
Sorry.

01:06:01.440 --> 01:06:02.786
[Astrid scoffs]

01:06:07.515 --> 01:06:10.380
♪ ♪

01:06:16.351 --> 01:06:18.664
[dragon snarling]

01:06:23.324 --> 01:06:26.016
Last chance. Make it count.

01:06:26.154 --> 01:06:28.329
[dragon sniffing]

01:06:32.298 --> 01:06:33.713
PHLEGMA:
Come on!

01:06:33.851 --> 01:06:35.577
- Go on, Astrid! You got it!
- Come on, Hiccup!

01:06:35.715 --> 01:06:38.201
- Go on!
- Come on!

01:06:39.512 --> 01:06:42.032
- [yells]
- [dragon moaning gently]

01:06:42.170 --> 01:06:43.413
No!

01:06:43.551 --> 01:06:46.036
Son of a half-troll,
rat-eating...

01:06:46.174 --> 01:06:47.900
Glad to see
she’s handling it gracefully.

01:06:48.038 --> 01:06:49.453
You!

01:06:49.591 --> 01:06:50.868
[clanking]

01:06:53.492 --> 01:06:55.735
Uh, okay.

01:06:55.873 --> 01:06:57.254
- Later.
- GOBBER: Hey, hey. Not so fast.

01:06:57.392 --> 01:06:58.773
- STOICK: Quiet down.
- No, I can’t.

01:06:58.911 --> 01:07:00.050
- I’m gonna be late for, uh...
- What?

01:07:00.188 --> 01:07:01.603
Late for what, exactly?

01:07:01.741 --> 01:07:03.053
- STOICK: Another year...
- [whispers]: Shut up.

01:07:03.191 --> 01:07:04.468
STOICK:
...and another Trial of Flame

01:07:04.606 --> 01:07:06.091
has come to an end.

01:07:06.229 --> 01:07:09.680
Elder Gothi has made
her decision.

01:07:11.751 --> 01:07:16.549
The new Top Slayer will be...

01:07:21.382 --> 01:07:24.005
- [crowd gasping]
- [Astrid gasps softly]

01:07:30.529 --> 01:07:31.530
[clanks]

01:07:31.668 --> 01:07:33.808
[crowd murmuring]

01:07:36.604 --> 01:07:37.950
[cheering and applause]

01:07:38.088 --> 01:07:40.090
[chuckles]
You’ve done it, Hiccup.

01:07:40.228 --> 01:07:41.885
You won the Trial of Flame.

01:07:42.023 --> 01:07:43.404
You get to kill the dragon.

01:07:43.542 --> 01:07:45.268
That’s my boy!

01:07:47.063 --> 01:07:48.892
[takes deep breath]

01:07:49.030 --> 01:07:52.206
Hiccup, you won!

01:07:52.344 --> 01:07:54.104
- [Hiccup gasps, grunts]
- [Gobber laughing]

01:07:54.242 --> 01:07:56.693
HICCUP:
Whoa! Yeah.

01:07:56.831 --> 01:07:58.246
Hooray me.

01:07:58.384 --> 01:07:59.972
I can’t wait to...

01:08:00.110 --> 01:08:02.319
Beat it and never come back.

01:08:02.457 --> 01:08:04.183
All right, bud. Time’s up.

01:08:04.321 --> 01:08:06.116
- ASTRID: My thoughts exactly.
- [gasps]

01:08:06.254 --> 01:08:08.153
Wh-What are you, uh...

01:08:08.291 --> 01:08:10.120
What are you doing here?

01:08:10.258 --> 01:08:12.018
- Looking for answers.
- Huh?

01:08:12.157 --> 01:08:13.503
What are you doing here?

01:08:13.641 --> 01:08:15.194
Who’s Bud? Your trainer?

01:08:15.332 --> 01:08:16.609
Did he dress you up in this?

01:08:16.747 --> 01:08:18.439
Uh, I-I know
this looks suspicious,

01:08:18.577 --> 01:08:20.751
- but f-funnily enough, I, uh...
- [rustling]

01:08:20.889 --> 01:08:23.168
Uh, you’re right!
You’re right. I, uh...

01:08:23.306 --> 01:08:24.824
I’m through with the lies.

01:08:24.962 --> 01:08:27.241
I’ve been making outfits,
so, um, you got me.

01:08:27.379 --> 01:08:28.311
It’s time everybody knew.

01:08:28.449 --> 01:08:29.795
Just take me back. [groans]

01:08:29.933 --> 01:08:31.417
Ow!

01:08:31.555 --> 01:08:32.625
Why would you do that?

01:08:32.763 --> 01:08:34.075
That’s for the lies.

01:08:34.213 --> 01:08:35.387
[Hiccup grunts]

01:08:35.525 --> 01:08:37.906
And that’s for everything else.

01:08:38.044 --> 01:08:39.356
- [Toothless growls softly]
- [gasps]

01:08:39.494 --> 01:08:41.324
HICCUP:
Oh, no.

01:08:41.462 --> 01:08:43.360
Run. Run!

01:08:43.498 --> 01:08:44.810
- No! No.
- [Toothless roars]

01:08:44.948 --> 01:08:46.639
- ASTRID: What...
- HICCUP: Toothless, no!

01:08:46.777 --> 01:08:47.951
Stop. It’s okay.

01:08:48.089 --> 01:08:50.643
She’s a friend. She’s a friend.

01:08:52.093 --> 01:08:54.164
[growls]

01:08:54.958 --> 01:08:58.030
Toothless, Astrid.
Astrid, Toothless.

01:08:58.168 --> 01:09:01.275
The, uh... the Night Fury.

01:09:02.828 --> 01:09:04.623
[snarls]

01:09:04.761 --> 01:09:06.625
[growling]

01:09:06.763 --> 01:09:08.799
I wouldn’t.

01:09:13.183 --> 01:09:14.805
We’re dead.

01:09:16.704 --> 01:09:19.396
Hey. Where do you think
you’re going?

01:09:19.534 --> 01:09:21.226
[panting]

01:09:21.364 --> 01:09:23.538
♪ ♪

01:09:25.506 --> 01:09:26.403
[yelps]

01:09:26.541 --> 01:09:28.716
[screaming]

01:09:32.996 --> 01:09:35.171
♪ ♪

01:09:39.554 --> 01:09:41.384
[grunting, panting]

01:09:41.522 --> 01:09:43.731
[birds screeching]

01:09:46.768 --> 01:09:48.736
[Toothless growls softly]

01:09:50.255 --> 01:09:52.567
ASTRID:
Hiccup! Get me down from here!

01:09:52.705 --> 01:09:54.569
HICCUP: You have to give me
a chance to explain.

01:09:54.707 --> 01:09:57.020
I’m not listening to anything
you have to say.

01:09:57.158 --> 01:09:58.849
Then I won’t speak.

01:09:58.987 --> 01:10:00.886
Just let us show you.

01:10:01.024 --> 01:10:03.095
Please, Astrid.

01:10:06.305 --> 01:10:09.205
- [Toothless growling softly]
- [Astrid grunting]

01:10:13.001 --> 01:10:14.417
[grunts]

01:10:14.555 --> 01:10:15.797
What is this?

01:10:15.935 --> 01:10:18.248
Uh, it’s my design.

01:10:19.076 --> 01:10:21.217
Yeah.
Pretty much the cocaptain.

01:10:22.045 --> 01:10:23.288
[Toothless groans]

01:10:23.426 --> 01:10:25.842
Then let’s get this over with.

01:10:26.774 --> 01:10:27.913
You got it.

01:10:28.051 --> 01:10:31.227
Toothless, let’s take her down.

01:10:32.228 --> 01:10:33.919
Gently.

01:10:34.885 --> 01:10:36.542
Nothing to be afraid of.

01:10:36.680 --> 01:10:39.407
[Astrid screaming]

01:10:39.545 --> 01:10:41.651
♪ ♪

01:10:43.273 --> 01:10:44.826
Oh, nice touch!

01:10:48.451 --> 01:10:50.004
I thought you were
his cocaptain!

01:10:50.142 --> 01:10:52.627
I am! It’s a temporary
dragon malfunction!

01:10:52.765 --> 01:10:56.182
[Astrid screaming, gasping]

01:10:56.321 --> 01:10:58.288
We worked out a whole system,
remember?

01:10:58.426 --> 01:11:00.048
[Astrid screams]

01:11:00.186 --> 01:11:02.913
ASTRID: If we survive,
I’m gonna kill you!

01:11:03.742 --> 01:11:05.675
[muffled grunting]

01:11:07.090 --> 01:11:08.781
- HICCUP: And now the spinning.
- [Astrid screams]

01:11:08.919 --> 01:11:12.302
Thank you for nothing,
you useless reptile.

01:11:12.440 --> 01:11:14.753
Please just make it stop.

01:11:14.891 --> 01:11:16.444
[Astrid screams]

01:11:16.582 --> 01:11:18.929
HICCUP: I’m clearly not
the one in control.

01:11:19.067 --> 01:11:20.345
ASTRID:
Then I’m sorry!

01:11:20.483 --> 01:11:23.313
Toothless, I’m sorry!

01:11:27.628 --> 01:11:29.802
[wind whistling]

01:11:33.116 --> 01:11:35.291
♪ ♪

01:11:54.171 --> 01:11:56.346
♪ ♪

01:12:18.506 --> 01:12:20.681
♪ ♪

01:12:40.977 --> 01:12:43.186
♪ ♪

01:13:03.379 --> 01:13:05.415
[moaning gently]

01:13:05.553 --> 01:13:07.037
Fine.

01:13:08.556 --> 01:13:10.420
You made your point.

01:13:12.629 --> 01:13:15.839
It doesn’t change the fact
you have to kill one tomorrow.

01:13:17.531 --> 01:13:18.946
But if we can change
your mind...

01:13:19.084 --> 01:13:20.603
What?

01:13:20.741 --> 01:13:22.708
You gonna take everyone up
for a magical ride?

01:13:25.608 --> 01:13:28.749
It won’t erase what they’ve
done to us, Hiccup.

01:13:29.681 --> 01:13:31.407
They hunt us, steal our food.

01:13:31.545 --> 01:13:33.236
And one of them took my mom.

01:13:33.374 --> 01:13:34.962
But do we just keep
killing one another?

01:13:35.100 --> 01:13:37.067
As opposed to...?

01:13:37.205 --> 01:13:39.276
I-I don’t know.

01:13:40.588 --> 01:13:44.281
But you botched
our escape plan, so I’m gonna need a minute.

01:13:48.009 --> 01:13:51.634
Well, I might
not snitch on you.

01:13:52.773 --> 01:13:55.016
And we might not
drop you in the sea.

01:13:55.154 --> 01:13:57.018
[Toothless grunting]

01:13:59.193 --> 01:14:01.851
HICCUP:
Bud? What’s up?

01:14:01.989 --> 01:14:03.300
What is it?

01:14:03.439 --> 01:14:06.096
- Hey. Hey.
- [Toothless roars]

01:14:07.235 --> 01:14:08.133
Get down!

01:14:08.271 --> 01:14:10.894
[dragons snarling]

01:14:11.032 --> 01:14:13.863
Toothless, get us out of here.

01:14:15.105 --> 01:14:17.936
[dragons shrieking, snarling]

01:14:18.902 --> 01:14:22.009
It looks like they’re
hauling in their kill.

01:14:22.147 --> 01:14:24.287
Then what does that make us?

01:14:25.909 --> 01:14:28.118
[hissing, snarling]

01:14:28.256 --> 01:14:30.500
♪ ♪

01:14:47.621 --> 01:14:50.382
[dragons shrieking, chittering]

01:14:57.009 --> 01:14:59.218
♪ ♪

01:15:00.081 --> 01:15:02.428
HICCUP:
The dragons’ nest.

01:15:03.499 --> 01:15:05.846
Oh, what my dad wouldn’t give
to find this.

01:15:14.751 --> 01:15:16.926
♪ ♪

01:15:24.554 --> 01:15:27.177
[chittering]

01:15:31.837 --> 01:15:34.046
[rumbling]

01:15:34.909 --> 01:15:37.049
[roaring]

01:15:39.811 --> 01:15:41.260
What is that?

01:15:41.398 --> 01:15:44.229
[deep roaring]

01:15:44.367 --> 01:15:45.886
All right, bud, time to go.

01:15:46.024 --> 01:15:48.371
♪ ♪

01:15:49.752 --> 01:15:51.408
[pained shrieking]

01:15:54.446 --> 01:15:57.483
ASTRID: I can’t believe it took
this long to figure it out.

01:15:57.622 --> 01:15:59.831
It all makes sense now.

01:15:59.969 --> 01:16:02.316
It’s like a giant beehive.

01:16:02.454 --> 01:16:04.801
They’re the workers,
and that’s their queen.

01:16:04.939 --> 01:16:06.078
Their alpha.

01:16:06.216 --> 01:16:07.735
It controls them.

01:16:07.873 --> 01:16:09.288
We got to find your dad.

01:16:09.426 --> 01:16:10.911
No, no, no, not yet.

01:16:11.049 --> 01:16:14.224
They’ll...
they’ll kill Toothless.

01:16:15.571 --> 01:16:19.954
Astrid, we have to think
this through carefully.

01:16:22.094 --> 01:16:25.753
Hiccup, we just discovered
the dragons’ nest,

01:16:25.891 --> 01:16:27.997
and you want
to keep it a secret?

01:16:28.135 --> 01:16:30.586
To protect your pet dragon?

01:16:31.414 --> 01:16:33.485
Are you serious?

01:16:34.382 --> 01:16:35.936
Yes.

01:16:45.186 --> 01:16:46.878
Okay.

01:16:48.086 --> 01:16:50.709
Then... what do we do?

01:16:54.679 --> 01:16:56.473
Just give me until tomorrow.

01:16:56.612 --> 01:16:58.475
I’ll figure it out.

01:17:01.030 --> 01:17:02.445
- [grunts]
- That’s for kidnapping me.

01:17:02.583 --> 01:17:05.448
Hey, are you gonna...

01:17:07.864 --> 01:17:11.143
And that’s for everything else.

01:17:12.489 --> 01:17:14.319
[chuckles softly]

01:17:14.457 --> 01:17:16.632
♪ ♪

01:17:21.015 --> 01:17:23.673
- [moans softly, grunts]
- What?

01:17:23.811 --> 01:17:27.090
[crowd cheering,
excited chatter]

01:17:34.097 --> 01:17:38.515
Well, I can finally show
my face in public again.

01:17:38.654 --> 01:17:41.277
[laughter]

01:17:42.796 --> 01:17:44.349
All right.

01:17:44.487 --> 01:17:48.249
If someone had told me
that in a few short weeks,

01:17:48.387 --> 01:17:53.151
Hiccup would’ve gone
from being, well, Hiccup...

01:17:53.289 --> 01:17:55.187
[laughter]

01:17:55.325 --> 01:17:58.535
...to placing first
in the Trial of Flame,

01:17:58.674 --> 01:18:00.399
I mean, I would’ve tied them
to a mast

01:18:00.537 --> 01:18:03.471
and shipped them off
for fear they’d gone mad.

01:18:03.609 --> 01:18:06.198
- [laughter]
- And you know it.

01:18:06.336 --> 01:18:08.097
[Stoick laughing]

01:18:09.305 --> 01:18:11.272
But here we are.

01:18:12.618 --> 01:18:16.588
My son has won the title
of Top Slayer.

01:18:17.693 --> 01:18:20.350
No one is more surprised...

01:18:23.077 --> 01:18:26.253
...or more proud than I am.

01:18:28.013 --> 01:18:32.569
Today, my boy
becomes a warrior.

01:18:32.708 --> 01:18:37.436
Today, he becomes one of us!

01:18:37.574 --> 01:18:40.439
- [cheering]
- Yeah!

01:18:40.577 --> 01:18:42.269
Yeah!

01:18:43.166 --> 01:18:44.547
Yeah!

01:18:45.410 --> 01:18:46.894
Yeah!

01:18:47.032 --> 01:18:49.552
CROWD [chanting]:
Hiccup! Hiccup! Hiccup!

01:18:49.690 --> 01:18:52.279
- Hiccup! Hiccup! Hiccup!
- [sighs]

01:18:52.417 --> 01:18:55.903
Hiccup! Hiccup! Hiccup!

01:18:56.041 --> 01:18:59.010
Hiccup! Hiccup! Hiccup! Hiccup!

01:18:59.148 --> 01:19:01.667
Hiccup! Hiccup! Hiccup!

01:19:01.806 --> 01:19:03.428
Hiccup! Hiccup!

01:19:03.566 --> 01:19:06.051
- Watch out for that dragon.
- [chanting continues]

01:19:07.604 --> 01:19:10.573
It’s not the dragon
I’m worried about. [chuckles]

01:19:12.851 --> 01:19:15.267
Look, I’m gonna try
to put an end to all this,

01:19:15.405 --> 01:19:19.133
but if something goes wrong
in there, just...

01:19:19.271 --> 01:19:20.479
don’t get involved.

01:19:20.617 --> 01:19:22.965
My dad respects you too much.

01:19:23.103 --> 01:19:25.346
[chanting continues faintly]

01:19:28.280 --> 01:19:29.972
Yeah.

01:19:30.110 --> 01:19:31.767
But...

01:19:31.905 --> 01:19:34.079
you have something I don’t.

01:19:34.977 --> 01:19:38.325
Something none of us have.

01:19:39.636 --> 01:19:44.193
So... I’m going
to stand by you,

01:19:44.331 --> 01:19:45.988
come what may.

01:19:49.129 --> 01:19:50.613
Come what may.

01:19:52.477 --> 01:19:53.892
It’s time, Hiccup.

01:19:57.620 --> 01:19:59.622
Knock him dead, son.

01:19:59.760 --> 01:20:02.349
[crowd cheering]

01:20:10.150 --> 01:20:13.049
CROWD [chanting]:
Hiccup! Hiccup! Hiccup!

01:20:13.187 --> 01:20:16.881
Hiccup! Hiccup! Hiccup! Hiccup!

01:20:17.019 --> 01:20:19.642
Hiccup! Hiccup! Hiccup!

01:20:19.780 --> 01:20:23.370
Hiccup! Hiccup! Hiccup! Hiccup!

01:20:23.508 --> 01:20:25.821
Hiccup! Hiccup!

01:20:25.959 --> 01:20:28.375
Hiccup! Hiccup! Hiccup! Hiccup!

01:20:28.513 --> 01:20:29.825
- Go, Hiccup!
- [chanting continues]

01:20:29.963 --> 01:20:31.827
Show ’em everything
I taught you!

01:20:31.965 --> 01:20:33.207
BOTH:
Should’ve been me.

01:20:33.345 --> 01:20:34.691
[sighs]

01:20:34.830 --> 01:20:36.417
Whew. All right?

01:20:36.555 --> 01:20:38.385
Good crowd, isn’t it?

01:20:38.523 --> 01:20:40.421
CROWD [chanting]:
Hiccup! Hiccup!

01:20:40.559 --> 01:20:44.287
Hiccup! Hiccup! Hiccup! Hiccup!

01:20:44.425 --> 01:20:46.634
[chanting fades]

01:20:56.472 --> 01:20:57.714
[exhales softly]

01:20:57.853 --> 01:20:59.509
I would have gone
with the hammer.

01:20:59.647 --> 01:21:01.995
Just-just give him a chance.

01:21:07.103 --> 01:21:09.381
[takes deep breath]

01:21:09.519 --> 01:21:11.004
I’m ready.

01:21:14.835 --> 01:21:16.802
[gate rattling]

01:21:16.941 --> 01:21:18.701
[clunking]

01:21:24.362 --> 01:21:26.122
[breathing heavily]

01:21:29.298 --> 01:21:32.128
- [whooshing]
- [crowd cheering]

01:21:35.338 --> 01:21:37.513
♪ ♪

01:21:40.792 --> 01:21:43.070
- [snarling]
- [indistinct shouting]

01:22:02.055 --> 01:22:04.678
[growling softly]

01:22:17.277 --> 01:22:19.658
What is he doing?

01:22:20.936 --> 01:22:22.799
I’m not gonna hurt you.

01:22:26.527 --> 01:22:28.771
[dragon hisses softly]

01:22:31.360 --> 01:22:34.018
I’m not one of them.

01:22:35.951 --> 01:22:38.091
[crowd gasping,
murmuring quietly]

01:22:46.444 --> 01:22:48.653
- Stop the fight.
- HICCUP: No.

01:22:48.791 --> 01:22:50.827
You all need to see this.

01:22:52.001 --> 01:22:53.969
They’re not
what we think they are.

01:22:55.315 --> 01:22:56.937
We don’t have to kill them.

01:22:58.318 --> 01:23:00.837
- I said stop the fight!
- [loud clang]

01:23:01.907 --> 01:23:04.772
[shrieking]

01:23:06.740 --> 01:23:09.260
[grunts] Out of my way!

01:23:09.812 --> 01:23:11.676
SNOTLOUT:
Get out of there, Hiccup!

01:23:11.814 --> 01:23:13.195
[rattling]

01:23:13.333 --> 01:23:14.920
Hiccup!

01:23:21.858 --> 01:23:24.551
[crowd gasping, yelling]

01:23:27.416 --> 01:23:29.590
[grunting]

01:23:32.007 --> 01:23:34.112
[roars]

01:23:34.733 --> 01:23:35.907
SNOTLOUT:
Quick, quick! Grab his hand!

01:23:36.045 --> 01:23:37.529
- Climb up.
- Hiccup, grab my hand!

01:23:37.667 --> 01:23:39.221
- SNOTLOUT: Get up here!
- RUFFNUT: Hurry up!

01:23:39.359 --> 01:23:40.394
SNOTLOUT: Get over here, man!
Just grab his hand!

01:23:40.532 --> 01:23:42.810
♪ ♪

01:23:48.816 --> 01:23:51.543
Astrid, get back here!

01:23:51.681 --> 01:23:53.476
That’s an order!

01:23:55.547 --> 01:23:57.446
[grunts]

01:23:58.240 --> 01:24:00.483
- [growls]
- [Hiccup gasps]

01:24:01.174 --> 01:24:02.347
STOICK:
Run!

01:24:02.485 --> 01:24:04.142
[straining]:
Come on.

01:24:05.385 --> 01:24:06.765
[snarls]

01:24:06.903 --> 01:24:08.284
STOICK:
Hiccup!

01:24:08.422 --> 01:24:09.596
[yelps]

01:24:09.734 --> 01:24:11.253
[gasping]

01:24:11.391 --> 01:24:12.737
[groaning]

01:24:12.875 --> 01:24:14.290
[Toothless squealing]

01:24:14.428 --> 01:24:16.637
[Toothless pants, squeals]

01:24:18.915 --> 01:24:21.608
- [crowd gasping]
- Night Fury.

01:24:22.609 --> 01:24:25.543
- VIKING: Night Fury!
- VIKING 2: He’s real!

01:24:29.133 --> 01:24:30.755
[shrieks]

01:24:30.893 --> 01:24:33.447
[crowd clamoring]

01:24:35.760 --> 01:24:38.003
[crowd exclaiming]

01:24:43.699 --> 01:24:46.184
[roars]

01:24:48.290 --> 01:24:50.499
[hissing]

01:24:50.637 --> 01:24:52.777
[clamoring, cheering]

01:24:52.915 --> 01:24:54.744
All right, bud. Go on. Go.

01:24:54.882 --> 01:24:56.712
- [shrieks]
- [Hiccup gasping]

01:24:57.471 --> 01:24:59.508
VIKING:
Go, go! Get to the side of him!

01:24:59.646 --> 01:25:02.131
[clamoring]

01:25:02.890 --> 01:25:04.444
Get out of the way, Hiccup!

01:25:04.582 --> 01:25:06.687
[clamoring continues]

01:25:06.825 --> 01:25:08.758
[screaming, grunting]

01:25:08.896 --> 01:25:10.243
No, stop.
You’re only making it worse!

01:25:10.381 --> 01:25:12.314
[gate rattling]

01:25:12.452 --> 01:25:13.625
Astrid!

01:25:13.763 --> 01:25:15.006
[Toothless roars]

01:25:15.144 --> 01:25:16.628
[groaning]

01:25:17.491 --> 01:25:19.148
I got it. Go!

01:25:20.977 --> 01:25:22.772
Stoick, he won’t hurt you.

01:25:22.910 --> 01:25:25.603
[Vikings shouting]

01:25:25.741 --> 01:25:27.570
[yells, grunts]

01:25:27.708 --> 01:25:29.365
[clamoring continues]

01:25:29.503 --> 01:25:31.850
- [Stoick grunting]
- [Toothless snarls]

01:25:32.955 --> 01:25:34.784
No!

01:25:36.441 --> 01:25:38.788
- [Toothless roars, hisses]
- [Stoick straining]

01:25:38.926 --> 01:25:40.790
HICCUP:
Toothless!

01:25:40.928 --> 01:25:42.067
Don’t.

01:25:42.206 --> 01:25:43.793
[moans softly]

01:25:43.931 --> 01:25:45.554
[grunts]

01:25:45.692 --> 01:25:48.557
- Take it down!
- [clamoring]

01:25:49.351 --> 01:25:50.455
VIKING:
Grab its legs!

01:25:50.593 --> 01:25:51.974
- Hold it down!
- HICCUP: No!

01:25:52.112 --> 01:25:54.632
- No, don’t hurt him!
- Stay back!

01:25:54.770 --> 01:25:56.358
[panting]

01:25:56.496 --> 01:25:58.291
[moaning softly]

01:25:59.740 --> 01:26:01.501
And you...

01:26:02.778 --> 01:26:04.159
[scoffs]

01:26:15.135 --> 01:26:17.068
Put it with the others.

01:26:20.658 --> 01:26:23.178
[whimpering]

01:26:23.316 --> 01:26:24.593
- STOICK: I should have known!
- Dad.

01:26:24.731 --> 01:26:26.111
- I should have seen the signs.
- Dad!

01:26:26.250 --> 01:26:27.285
We had a deal!

01:26:27.423 --> 01:26:29.011
I-I know,
but that was before...

01:26:29.149 --> 01:26:30.909
It’s all so messed up.

01:26:31.047 --> 01:26:35.293
So everything in the ring,
what, a-a trick? A lie?

01:26:35.431 --> 01:26:37.537
No, I-I should have told you
before now.

01:26:37.675 --> 01:26:39.470
Take that out on me--
it’s my fault--

01:26:39.608 --> 01:26:41.782
but please
don’t hurt Toothless.

01:26:42.852 --> 01:26:44.820
The dragon?

01:26:44.958 --> 01:26:47.236
That’s what you’re
worried about?

01:26:47.374 --> 01:26:49.307
Not the people
you almost killed?

01:26:49.445 --> 01:26:51.551
He’s not dangerous.
He-he was protecting me.

01:26:51.689 --> 01:26:55.348
They took your mother,
for gods’ sake!

01:26:56.521 --> 01:26:59.869
If she could see you now
standing there with them

01:27:00.007 --> 01:27:01.906
when they’ve killed
hundreds of us.

01:27:02.044 --> 01:27:03.563
And we’ve killed
thousands of them!

01:27:03.701 --> 01:27:05.185
- [grunts in frustration]
- They defend themselves.

01:27:05.323 --> 01:27:06.566
That’s all.

01:27:06.704 --> 01:27:08.050
They raid us
because they have to.

01:27:08.188 --> 01:27:09.465
If they don’t bring
enough food back,

01:27:09.603 --> 01:27:10.984
they’ll be eaten themselves.

01:27:11.122 --> 01:27:12.882
There’s something else
on their island.

01:27:13.020 --> 01:27:14.574
A dragon like I’ve never seen.

01:27:14.712 --> 01:27:16.472
Their island?

01:27:18.060 --> 01:27:19.889
You’ve been to the nest.

01:27:20.752 --> 01:27:22.271
Did I say nest?

01:27:22.409 --> 01:27:24.239
How did you find it?

01:27:24.377 --> 01:27:26.171
I didn’t. Toothless did.

01:27:26.310 --> 01:27:28.898
Only a dragon
can find the island.

01:27:32.247 --> 01:27:34.697
No. Dad, no.

01:27:34.835 --> 01:27:36.181
You don’t know
what you’re up against.

01:27:36.320 --> 01:27:38.632
This is nothing like
you’ve ever seen.

01:27:38.770 --> 01:27:40.358
You can’t win this one.

01:27:40.496 --> 01:27:42.153
For once in your life,
would you please

01:27:42.291 --> 01:27:43.775
- just listen to me?
- [grunts aggressively]

01:27:43.913 --> 01:27:45.639
[grunts]

01:27:48.055 --> 01:27:50.955
You’ve thrown your lot
in with them.

01:27:52.301 --> 01:27:54.407
You’re not one of us.

01:27:54.545 --> 01:27:56.650
You’re not my son.

01:28:02.898 --> 01:28:05.694
[door creaking shut]

01:28:05.832 --> 01:28:07.178
STOICK:
Ready the ships!

01:28:07.316 --> 01:28:09.801
We sail at dawn!

01:28:09.939 --> 01:28:12.597
[breathing heavily]

01:28:17.568 --> 01:28:20.640
[distressed groaning]

01:28:20.778 --> 01:28:22.642
[busy chatter]

01:28:24.333 --> 01:28:26.680
[groaning softly]

01:28:26.818 --> 01:28:28.993
♪ ♪

01:28:32.686 --> 01:28:35.310
[indistinct shouting]

01:28:36.172 --> 01:28:38.347
[groaning]

01:28:38.485 --> 01:28:40.556
VIKING:
Forward on the leading line!

01:28:40.694 --> 01:28:41.833
Swing it out slightly.

01:28:41.971 --> 01:28:43.559
Here she comes. Easy.

01:28:43.697 --> 01:28:45.630
Careful with the head.

01:28:46.528 --> 01:28:48.219
- [muffled growling]
- Oh, careful now.

01:28:48.357 --> 01:28:50.221
PHLEGMA:
Weapons loaded!

01:28:50.359 --> 01:28:52.016
SPITELOUT:
Spare rigging aboard?

01:28:52.154 --> 01:28:54.225
- Aye.
- Hoist the sails!

01:28:54.363 --> 01:28:55.951
Aye, Chief.

01:28:58.609 --> 01:29:01.025
- Ready the oars.
- Aye, Stoick.

01:29:02.164 --> 01:29:05.374
We set sail for Helheim’s Gate!

01:29:22.426 --> 01:29:24.531
Lead us home, devil.

01:29:24.669 --> 01:29:27.016
[Toothless growls softly]

01:29:27.154 --> 01:29:29.364
♪ ♪

01:29:35.542 --> 01:29:38.373
[moans softly]

01:29:41.997 --> 01:29:44.206
[wind howling]

01:29:55.148 --> 01:29:56.805
I tried to stop them.

01:29:57.633 --> 01:30:00.187
I ended up giving them
exactly what they wanted.

01:30:03.432 --> 01:30:05.676
I should’ve just...

01:30:05.814 --> 01:30:08.541
I should’ve killed him when
I found him in those woods.

01:30:10.612 --> 01:30:12.786
It would have been better
for everyone.

01:30:12.924 --> 01:30:14.236
Yeah.

01:30:14.374 --> 01:30:16.376
The rest of us
would have done it.

01:30:19.137 --> 01:30:20.587
So, why didn’t you?

01:30:21.381 --> 01:30:22.796
- Why didn’t you?
- I don’t know.

01:30:22.934 --> 01:30:24.384
- I-I couldn’t.
- That’s not an answer.

01:30:24.522 --> 01:30:26.110
Why is this so important to you
all of a sudden?

01:30:26.248 --> 01:30:28.284
Because I want to remember
what you say right now.

01:30:28.423 --> 01:30:30.286
For the love of...
Because I was weak.

01:30:30.425 --> 01:30:32.012
Because I was a coward,
because I wouldn’t

01:30:32.150 --> 01:30:33.669
- kill a dragon.
- You said "wouldn’t" that time.

01:30:33.807 --> 01:30:35.568
Whatever! I wouldn’t!

01:30:35.706 --> 01:30:38.191
I’m the first Viking
in who knows how long

01:30:38.329 --> 01:30:40.745
who wouldn’t kill a dragon.

01:30:41.919 --> 01:30:44.473
First to ride one, though.

01:30:50.168 --> 01:30:52.205
So?

01:30:55.104 --> 01:30:57.417
I wouldn’t kill him because...

01:30:58.660 --> 01:31:00.903
...he looked
just as frightened as I was.

01:31:01.041 --> 01:31:03.250
♪ ♪

01:31:04.320 --> 01:31:07.185
When I looked at him...

01:31:07.323 --> 01:31:09.464
I saw myself.

01:31:19.474 --> 01:31:21.648
Bet he’s really frightened now.

01:31:28.344 --> 01:31:29.967
What are you gonna do about it?

01:31:30.105 --> 01:31:31.555
Eh.

01:31:32.487 --> 01:31:34.074
Probably something stupid.

01:31:34.212 --> 01:31:35.904
Hmm.

01:31:36.042 --> 01:31:37.871
Well, you’ve already done that.

01:31:43.359 --> 01:31:44.809
Then something crazy.

01:31:46.397 --> 01:31:48.503
That’s more like it.

01:31:49.504 --> 01:31:51.678
♪ ♪

01:31:54.198 --> 01:31:55.786
Sound your positions.

01:31:55.924 --> 01:31:57.546
Stay within earshot.

01:31:57.684 --> 01:31:59.997
SNORTI:
One length to your stern.

01:32:00.135 --> 01:32:02.378
LOOGI:
On your starboard flank.

01:32:02.517 --> 01:32:04.588
FUNGI:
Why aren’t they attacking?

01:32:04.726 --> 01:32:06.969
Maybe they know
something we don’t.

01:32:09.903 --> 01:32:11.733
Are you just a glutton
for punishment or what?

01:32:11.871 --> 01:32:14.667
We have a fighting chance
this time.

01:32:16.323 --> 01:32:18.567
Thanks to Hiccup.

01:32:18.705 --> 01:32:20.189
GOBBER: How long
do you think we’re gonna...

01:32:20.327 --> 01:32:22.847
- STOICK: Shh.
- [Toothless purring softly]

01:32:32.201 --> 01:32:34.272
Step aside, Drül.

01:32:34.410 --> 01:32:36.585
♪ ♪

01:32:39.519 --> 01:32:41.728
[continues purring softly]

01:32:44.904 --> 01:32:47.803
[grunting]

01:32:49.460 --> 01:32:52.428
- SPITELOUT: Ship the oars!
- STOICK: Oars in.

01:32:57.123 --> 01:32:59.677
[continues purring softly]

01:33:05.614 --> 01:33:07.409
SNOTLOUT:
<i>Okay, wait.</i>

01:33:07.547 --> 01:33:10.895
You just disgraced yourself
in front of the whole village.

01:33:11.033 --> 01:33:13.104
- Why would we listen to you?
- ’Cause I said so.

01:33:13.242 --> 01:33:15.313
Exactly. Pay attention, gang.

01:33:15.451 --> 01:33:18.006
Look, my dad means well,
but he’s stubborn.

01:33:18.144 --> 01:33:20.008
And he’s about to be
way in over his head,

01:33:20.146 --> 01:33:21.112
so it’s up to us.

01:33:21.250 --> 01:33:22.666
Us?

01:33:22.804 --> 01:33:24.668
I can’t pull this off
without you guys.

01:33:24.806 --> 01:33:26.635
And you all have
something special to offer.

01:33:26.773 --> 01:33:28.533
Say no more.

01:33:28.672 --> 01:33:31.985
You were wise to seek
the world’s most deadly weapon.

01:33:32.123 --> 01:33:33.538
It’s me.

01:33:33.677 --> 01:33:35.023
You’ve got a wild side,
and I like it.

01:33:35.161 --> 01:33:36.058
Astrid, you’re
our strongest fighter.

01:33:36.196 --> 01:33:37.163
We need you to lead us.

01:33:37.301 --> 01:33:39.510
Lead us where exactly?

01:33:39.648 --> 01:33:43.100
They left
with every ship we have.

01:33:45.447 --> 01:33:47.035
Stick with me.

01:33:51.280 --> 01:33:52.661
GOBBER:
Oh.

01:33:52.799 --> 01:33:55.146
That’s where that went.

01:33:55.284 --> 01:33:57.977
Stay low. Be ready.

01:34:02.671 --> 01:34:04.846
♪ ♪

01:34:09.436 --> 01:34:11.991
[breathing heavily]

01:34:19.584 --> 01:34:22.553
[moaning]

01:34:24.417 --> 01:34:26.557
[grunts]

01:34:27.592 --> 01:34:30.492
[breathing heavily]

01:34:33.219 --> 01:34:35.186
[distant rustling]

01:34:36.671 --> 01:34:38.569
We’re here.

01:34:39.466 --> 01:34:40.847
[growls softly]

01:34:40.985 --> 01:34:43.816
[sniffing]

01:34:50.201 --> 01:34:52.410
[trembling breaths]

01:34:56.000 --> 01:34:57.726
- No, uh-uh.
- [snarls]

01:34:58.589 --> 01:35:01.040
Hiccup, I...

01:35:01.178 --> 01:35:03.249
Relax.

01:35:06.045 --> 01:35:07.115
It’s okay.

01:35:07.253 --> 01:35:09.980
[moaning softly]

01:35:10.118 --> 01:35:12.258
[growls]

01:35:17.470 --> 01:35:19.575
Uh, where are you going?

01:35:19.714 --> 01:35:21.923
HICCUP: You’re gonna need
something to help you hold on.

01:35:22.061 --> 01:35:23.890
Get ready.

01:35:24.028 --> 01:35:26.030
It’s gonna be a long night.
[grunts]

01:35:26.168 --> 01:35:28.619
[dragons chittering]

01:35:32.830 --> 01:35:34.936
VIKING:
Form a defensive line.

01:35:35.074 --> 01:35:37.145
[grunting, busy chatter]

01:35:37.283 --> 01:35:39.043
[tools clanking]

01:35:40.873 --> 01:35:43.254
VIKING:
Sharpen those axes, lads!

01:35:43.392 --> 01:35:45.809
♪ ♪

01:35:51.366 --> 01:35:53.195
Chief.

01:35:53.333 --> 01:35:54.887
Ready, Chief.

01:35:56.095 --> 01:35:59.684
- Stand strong.
- Aye, Stoick.

01:35:59.823 --> 01:36:02.826
- Make your people proud.
- We will, Stoick.

01:36:05.069 --> 01:36:07.106
Today, we destroy

01:36:07.244 --> 01:36:11.420
the reign of the dragon
once and for all.

01:36:15.942 --> 01:36:19.843
However this ends,
it ends right here, right now!

01:36:19.981 --> 01:36:21.499
[Vikings grunting rhythmically]

01:36:21.637 --> 01:36:25.089
So let’s send these devils
back to hell!

01:36:25.227 --> 01:36:27.643
[cheering]

01:36:32.787 --> 01:36:34.961
♪ ♪

01:36:36.480 --> 01:36:38.689
[Vikings shouting indistinctly]

01:36:45.489 --> 01:36:47.698
[rumbling]

01:36:55.879 --> 01:36:58.122
[breathing heavily]

01:37:04.163 --> 01:37:07.028
[dragons chittering]

01:37:12.033 --> 01:37:13.586
[yells]

01:37:13.724 --> 01:37:16.451
- [Vikings yelling]
- [dragons shrieking]

01:37:36.678 --> 01:37:39.060
[distressed moaning]

01:37:43.064 --> 01:37:44.720
Is that it?

01:37:44.859 --> 01:37:46.067
The nest is ours!

01:37:46.205 --> 01:37:48.414
[Vikings cheering]

01:37:49.829 --> 01:37:52.107
This isn’t over.

01:37:53.039 --> 01:37:54.903
[rumbling]

01:37:57.699 --> 01:37:59.977
[dragon growling]

01:38:00.115 --> 01:38:01.979
Get clear!

01:38:02.117 --> 01:38:03.636
Fall back!

01:38:03.774 --> 01:38:05.741
GOBBER:
Fall back! Everyone, fall back!

01:38:05.880 --> 01:38:08.054
♪ ♪

01:38:12.058 --> 01:38:13.232
Retreat!

01:38:13.370 --> 01:38:15.717
[frantic shouting, screaming]

01:38:15.855 --> 01:38:17.236
Move!

01:38:19.238 --> 01:38:21.757
[roaring]

01:38:30.525 --> 01:38:33.114
[frantic shouting]

01:38:36.013 --> 01:38:37.704
[growls]

01:38:39.016 --> 01:38:40.949
[frantic shouting continues]

01:38:41.087 --> 01:38:43.089
[screaming]

01:38:45.298 --> 01:38:47.404
Get to the ships!

01:38:47.542 --> 01:38:48.923
No!

01:38:51.891 --> 01:38:54.100
[screaming]

01:38:57.621 --> 01:39:00.417
[distressed moaning,
whimpering]

01:39:01.659 --> 01:39:03.454
Get to the far side
of the island.

01:39:03.592 --> 01:39:05.284
Aye, Chief. Let’s move!

01:39:05.422 --> 01:39:07.976
This way! All of you!

01:39:13.326 --> 01:39:15.432
- Get out of here, lads!
- Follow me!

01:39:15.570 --> 01:39:17.261
Gobber, go with the others.

01:39:17.399 --> 01:39:20.299
Why? Where are you going?

01:39:21.162 --> 01:39:23.785
[grunting]

01:39:27.444 --> 01:39:28.963
Actually,
I’m gonna stick around.

01:39:29.101 --> 01:39:31.206
You’ve got that wild look
in your eye.

01:39:32.311 --> 01:39:34.485
STOICK: I can buy them
some time if I give that thing

01:39:34.623 --> 01:39:35.659
something to hunt.

01:39:35.797 --> 01:39:37.350
And I can double that time.

01:39:37.488 --> 01:39:38.765
[chuckles]

01:39:38.903 --> 01:39:40.698
I know. I’m a big softy.

01:39:41.492 --> 01:39:44.461
Softest part of you
is your teeth.

01:39:44.599 --> 01:39:47.533
[growling]

01:39:49.707 --> 01:39:52.020
[Stoick and Gobber
whooping and yelling]

01:39:59.510 --> 01:40:01.202
[both gasp]

01:40:01.340 --> 01:40:04.032
♪ ♪

01:40:06.172 --> 01:40:08.692
[roaring]

01:40:09.520 --> 01:40:12.730
[growling]

01:40:13.559 --> 01:40:17.011
Remember,
that thing is their queen.

01:40:17.149 --> 01:40:18.736
They’re inclined to do
whatever it says.

01:40:18.874 --> 01:40:20.635
We’ve got to help them
fight back.

01:40:20.773 --> 01:40:22.809
[gasps]

01:40:23.638 --> 01:40:25.019
HICCUP:
Fishlegs, what do we got?

01:40:25.157 --> 01:40:27.987
Ooh, uh, heavily armored
skull and tail,

01:40:28.125 --> 01:40:30.334
perfect for bashing
and crushing.

01:40:30.472 --> 01:40:32.716
Small eyes, large nostrils.

01:40:32.854 --> 01:40:34.787
Relies on hearing and smell.

01:40:34.925 --> 01:40:37.445
- Got it. Astrid.
- ASTRID: Okay.

01:40:37.583 --> 01:40:40.517
Snotlout, Fishlegs,
hang in its blind spot.

01:40:40.655 --> 01:40:43.382
Make some noise.
Keep it confused.

01:40:43.520 --> 01:40:46.005
Ruff, Tuff,
figure out its shot limit.

01:40:46.143 --> 01:40:47.282
Make it mad.

01:40:47.420 --> 01:40:49.698
TUFFNUT:
That’s our specialty!

01:40:51.148 --> 01:40:53.116
FISHLEGS:
Try not to get killed, guys!

01:40:56.636 --> 01:40:59.087
- [flame whooshing]
- [screaming]

01:41:03.160 --> 01:41:06.474
Uh, this thing doesn’t have
a blind spot.

01:41:10.064 --> 01:41:11.996
There!

01:41:16.484 --> 01:41:18.762
[grunts] Hey, bud.

01:41:18.900 --> 01:41:20.281
[stammering]:
I’m good.

01:41:20.419 --> 01:41:21.799
Be careful.

01:41:22.593 --> 01:41:26.183
- [coughing]
- [Toothless moaning softly]

01:41:26.321 --> 01:41:28.875
I know, I know,
but I’m, uh... I’m here now.

01:41:29.013 --> 01:41:31.775
[Toothless moaning, whining]

01:41:35.606 --> 01:41:38.816
- [snarling]
- [grunting]

01:41:40.439 --> 01:41:41.819
[grunting]

01:41:41.957 --> 01:41:43.511
SNOTLOUT:
Keep hammering!

01:41:43.649 --> 01:41:46.514
But we’re confusing
our own dragons!

01:41:46.652 --> 01:41:48.654
SNOTLOUT:
Oh, no!

01:41:48.792 --> 01:41:51.105
[Snotlout screaming]

01:41:54.798 --> 01:41:56.386
- [grunts, groans]
- SPITELOUT: This way!

01:41:56.524 --> 01:41:58.077
This way! Come on! Come on!

01:41:58.215 --> 01:41:59.803
VIKING: Guys, keep moving!
Keep moving! Come on!

01:41:59.941 --> 01:42:00.873
PHLEGMA:
Go!

01:42:01.011 --> 01:42:02.633
Is that my kid?

01:42:02.771 --> 01:42:05.360
- FISHLEGS: Snotlout!
- Come on! Throw it!

01:42:05.498 --> 01:42:07.535
[grunting]

01:42:07.673 --> 01:42:09.709
Whoa, girl. [whimpers]

01:42:09.847 --> 01:42:11.504
Going down.

01:42:12.471 --> 01:42:13.955
[grunts]

01:42:14.093 --> 01:42:15.819
I’m okay.

01:42:15.957 --> 01:42:17.993
[groaning]:
Less okay.

01:42:18.132 --> 01:42:19.857
[growling]

01:42:19.995 --> 01:42:22.308
- [screams]
- I got you, Fishlegs.

01:42:22.446 --> 01:42:23.689
[yells]

01:42:23.827 --> 01:42:25.346
[roaring]

01:42:31.110 --> 01:42:32.353
What’s wrong?

01:42:32.491 --> 01:42:34.976
Got something in your eye?

01:42:35.114 --> 01:42:38.428
Yeah! Now, that’s a Top Slayer.

01:42:40.326 --> 01:42:42.604
[Snotlout yells]

01:42:43.467 --> 01:42:45.676
[grunting]

01:42:45.814 --> 01:42:47.506
[Toothless whining]

01:42:47.644 --> 01:42:49.163
[straining]

01:42:51.441 --> 01:42:52.338
[Hiccup grunts]

01:42:52.476 --> 01:42:55.307
[Toothless sputtering]

01:43:05.420 --> 01:43:07.319
[grunting]

01:43:13.221 --> 01:43:15.258
[exclaims]

01:43:18.157 --> 01:43:20.366
[coughing]

01:43:20.504 --> 01:43:23.438
[breathing heavily]

01:43:23.576 --> 01:43:26.372
[Hiccup coughing, panting]

01:43:26.510 --> 01:43:28.685
[muffled splash]

01:43:50.051 --> 01:43:52.226
♪ ♪

01:43:53.019 --> 01:43:54.918
[grunts]

01:43:57.023 --> 01:43:58.093
[roars softly]

01:43:58.232 --> 01:43:59.923
You got it, bud.

01:44:05.687 --> 01:44:07.241
Hiccup.

01:44:09.553 --> 01:44:12.349
I was only trying
to protect you.

01:44:12.487 --> 01:44:14.938
I know, Dad.

01:44:15.076 --> 01:44:17.147
Let me return the favor.

01:44:19.632 --> 01:44:21.703
Whatever happens up there,

01:44:21.841 --> 01:44:25.742
I’m proud to call you my son.

01:44:29.711 --> 01:44:31.299
And that’s all I need.

01:44:32.783 --> 01:44:34.095
Let’s go.

01:44:35.061 --> 01:44:37.271
[Toothless roaring]

01:44:38.306 --> 01:44:39.618
He’s up!

01:44:40.895 --> 01:44:42.655
You two, get Snotlout.

01:44:42.793 --> 01:44:44.243
I’ll distract the queen.

01:44:44.381 --> 01:44:46.141
[growling]

01:44:46.280 --> 01:44:49.421
That’s right. Eyes on me.

01:44:51.630 --> 01:44:52.976
RUFFNUT and TUFFNUT:
Snotlout!

01:44:53.114 --> 01:44:55.323
- [trembling breaths]
- [dragon growling]

01:44:56.497 --> 01:44:57.567
Now!

01:44:57.705 --> 01:45:00.155
Oh, you have got
to be kidding me.

01:45:01.087 --> 01:45:03.435
[yelling]

01:45:06.748 --> 01:45:08.371
Whoa!

01:45:11.477 --> 01:45:13.168
[heavy, gasping breaths]

01:45:13.307 --> 01:45:14.894
I can’t believe that worked.

01:45:15.032 --> 01:45:17.241
[chuckles] Yeah.

01:45:17.380 --> 01:45:18.760
[dragon roaring]

01:45:18.898 --> 01:45:21.660
- [chittering]
- ASTRID: No, no, no, girl.

01:45:21.798 --> 01:45:24.318
Fight it! Don’t listen to her!

01:45:24.456 --> 01:45:25.905
Shake it off!

01:45:26.043 --> 01:45:27.666
[grunts]

01:45:31.911 --> 01:45:34.466
[shrieking]

01:45:34.604 --> 01:45:36.295
[yells, grunts]

01:45:38.780 --> 01:45:40.886
[grunting]

01:45:41.024 --> 01:45:42.888
[pained groaning]

01:45:44.027 --> 01:45:45.408
[yelps]

01:45:45.546 --> 01:45:47.996
[grunting]

01:45:48.134 --> 01:45:50.344
[pained groaning]

01:45:50.482 --> 01:45:52.380
Astrid.

01:45:53.864 --> 01:45:57.143
[grunting]

01:46:01.044 --> 01:46:02.390
[yells]

01:46:02.528 --> 01:46:05.013
[whooshing]

01:46:07.326 --> 01:46:09.259
Did you get her?

01:46:11.157 --> 01:46:12.262
[grunts]

01:46:12.400 --> 01:46:14.575
♪ ♪

01:46:22.859 --> 01:46:24.239
Go.

01:46:27.242 --> 01:46:28.934
That thing has wings.

01:46:29.072 --> 01:46:31.005
Let’s see if it can use them.

01:46:38.253 --> 01:46:41.671
- [whooshing]
- [roars]

01:46:46.192 --> 01:46:48.125
You think that did it?

01:46:48.263 --> 01:46:50.231
[roaring]

01:46:50.369 --> 01:46:51.577
Yep.

01:46:52.751 --> 01:46:54.684
[indistinct shouting]

01:46:56.858 --> 01:46:59.205
[roaring]

01:47:06.765 --> 01:47:09.664
All right, bud.
It’s time to disappear.

01:47:14.980 --> 01:47:17.465
- Here it comes!
- [flame whooshing]

01:47:22.988 --> 01:47:25.784
Quite the chief you have
in the making there.

01:47:25.922 --> 01:47:27.164
Aye.

01:47:32.446 --> 01:47:34.620
♪ ♪

01:47:40.074 --> 01:47:42.248
[roaring]

01:47:44.768 --> 01:47:47.840
- [whooshing]
- [roars]

01:47:53.328 --> 01:47:56.573
- [whooshing]
- [Vikings gasping]

01:47:59.300 --> 01:48:02.648
[pained roaring]

01:48:08.171 --> 01:48:09.828
Watch out!

01:48:13.556 --> 01:48:15.040
Okay, time’s up.

01:48:15.178 --> 01:48:17.076
Let’s see if this works.

01:48:22.219 --> 01:48:23.773
Is that all you’ve got?

01:48:23.911 --> 01:48:25.257
[roars]

01:48:42.964 --> 01:48:44.483
Stay with me, bud!

01:48:44.621 --> 01:48:46.485
Just a little bit longer!

01:48:47.555 --> 01:48:49.315
Hold, Toothless!

01:48:51.835 --> 01:48:53.527
Now!

01:48:56.391 --> 01:48:58.186
[yells]

01:48:58.324 --> 01:48:59.843
[sputtering]

01:49:02.466 --> 01:49:04.676
[sparks crackling]

01:49:10.095 --> 01:49:12.373
- [Vikings gasping, screaming]
- [explosive whooshing]

01:49:12.511 --> 01:49:15.100
[whimpering]

01:49:15.238 --> 01:49:17.447
Yeah, bud, we... No!

01:49:22.935 --> 01:49:25.559
[roaring]

01:49:36.604 --> 01:49:38.779
STOICK [faintly]:
Hiccup!

01:49:43.059 --> 01:49:45.095
Hiccup?

01:49:45.233 --> 01:49:46.718
Son?

01:49:48.547 --> 01:49:50.549
Hiccup!

01:49:55.519 --> 01:49:57.245
[Toothless grunts softly]

01:50:05.460 --> 01:50:07.255
Oh, son.

01:50:09.119 --> 01:50:10.880
[Toothless groans weakly]

01:50:11.018 --> 01:50:12.675
[sobs softly]

01:50:19.474 --> 01:50:21.476
I’m so sorry.

01:50:25.032 --> 01:50:26.792
[moans softly]

01:50:31.314 --> 01:50:33.523
♪ ♪

01:50:47.330 --> 01:50:49.850
[dragon grumbling]

01:50:59.169 --> 01:51:01.309
[soft, trembling breaths]

01:51:21.329 --> 01:51:23.987
[moans softly]

01:51:33.410 --> 01:51:35.171
STOICK:
Hiccup.

01:51:35.999 --> 01:51:38.346
[grunting]

01:51:43.213 --> 01:51:45.353
He’s alive. He’s alive!

01:51:45.491 --> 01:51:48.391
[Vikings cheering]

01:51:48.529 --> 01:51:50.048
Yeah!

01:51:50.186 --> 01:51:52.222
Yes!

01:52:01.680 --> 01:52:02.888
[moans softly]

01:52:03.026 --> 01:52:05.166
STOICK:
Thank you...

01:52:06.064 --> 01:52:08.238
...for saving my son.

01:52:09.584 --> 01:52:12.587
Well, you know...
[chuckles] most of him.

01:52:14.141 --> 01:52:16.315
♪ ♪

01:52:22.563 --> 01:52:25.152
[sighs]

01:52:28.465 --> 01:52:30.088
Hey, Toothless.

01:52:30.951 --> 01:52:31.952
[grunts]

01:52:32.090 --> 01:52:33.332
Okay.

01:52:33.470 --> 01:52:35.231
[panting]

01:52:38.821 --> 01:52:40.650
I’m in my house.

01:52:42.169 --> 01:52:43.791
You-You’re in my house.

01:52:43.929 --> 01:52:46.483
D-Does my dad know you’re here?

01:52:46.621 --> 01:52:49.107
Oh, come on.

01:52:51.247 --> 01:52:53.076
[Toothless moans softly]

01:53:05.744 --> 01:53:07.953
[sniffing]

01:53:08.091 --> 01:53:10.231
[moans softly]

01:53:15.650 --> 01:53:17.238
[sighs]

01:53:17.376 --> 01:53:20.621
[takes deep breath]

01:53:22.865 --> 01:53:24.694
[groans softly]

01:53:31.287 --> 01:53:33.807
- [grunts]
- [Toothless moaning]

01:53:37.017 --> 01:53:38.639
Thanks, bud.

01:53:38.777 --> 01:53:40.952
♪ ♪

01:53:42.194 --> 01:53:44.196
Okay, here we go.

01:53:45.128 --> 01:53:46.992
[grunts]

01:53:47.130 --> 01:53:50.202
[breathing heavily]

01:53:55.449 --> 01:53:57.658
[Toothless moans gently]

01:54:10.429 --> 01:54:11.914
[dragon shrieks]

01:54:12.052 --> 01:54:13.570
[panting]

01:54:13.708 --> 01:54:15.331
Toothless, stay.

01:54:15.469 --> 01:54:17.367
[grunts]

01:54:19.059 --> 01:54:21.785
Hey, hey, hey!
Shouldn’t you be in bed?

01:54:21.924 --> 01:54:23.373
[Vikings chattering]

01:54:23.511 --> 01:54:25.686
Okay. Hold on tight, guys.

01:54:25.824 --> 01:54:28.137
Here we go.

01:54:28.275 --> 01:54:29.966
Whoa, whoa!

01:54:30.760 --> 01:54:33.004
[whooping, laughter,
indistinct chatter]

01:54:33.867 --> 01:54:35.869
[indistinct busy chatter]

01:54:36.731 --> 01:54:38.319
Hey! Hey!

01:54:38.457 --> 01:54:40.874
- There you go!
- [chitters playfully]

01:54:41.702 --> 01:54:44.118
[dragons chittering]

01:54:45.223 --> 01:54:48.536
- There he is! Oh, oh.
- Oh! Okay.

01:54:49.399 --> 01:54:51.643
STOICK:
So, what do you think?

01:54:51.781 --> 01:54:54.094
A few changes
since you’ve been out.

01:54:54.232 --> 01:54:57.856
Flying back here was, uh, quite
an experience, let me tell you.

01:54:57.994 --> 01:55:00.617
Wait, wait, you...
you rode a dragon?

01:55:00.755 --> 01:55:02.102
Well... well,
that monster burned

01:55:02.240 --> 01:55:03.758
all of our ships,
so we didn’t really

01:55:03.897 --> 01:55:05.243
- have much of a...
- ASTRID: Hiccup!

01:55:05.381 --> 01:55:06.692
HICCUP:
Oh, no.

01:55:06.830 --> 01:55:08.694
What’d I do this time?

01:55:08.832 --> 01:55:09.764
Ow!

01:55:09.903 --> 01:55:11.456
That’s for scaring me.

01:55:11.594 --> 01:55:13.907
Okay, is it always gonna
be like this? ’Cause...

01:55:16.702 --> 01:55:19.257
And that’s for everything else.

01:55:19.395 --> 01:55:22.156
You know, ’cause... ’cause I...
I-I could get used to that.

01:55:22.294 --> 01:55:23.882
STOICK:
Yep.

01:55:24.020 --> 01:55:28.991
Turns out all we needed
was a little more of this.

01:55:29.750 --> 01:55:31.614
You just gestured to all of me.

01:55:31.752 --> 01:55:34.720
Well, you know, most of you.

01:55:34.858 --> 01:55:37.033
New leg is my handiwork
with just a dash

01:55:37.171 --> 01:55:39.656
of your kooky flair
thrown in for good measure.

01:55:39.794 --> 01:55:40.830
Here we go.

01:55:40.968 --> 01:55:42.349
[grunts] Welcome home.

01:55:42.487 --> 01:55:43.764
- You rebuilt it?
- Yeah.

01:55:43.902 --> 01:55:45.662
I found your designs.

01:55:45.800 --> 01:55:47.285
Not too bad.

01:55:47.423 --> 01:55:49.494
- [snarling playfully]
- Night Fury! [laughs]

01:55:49.632 --> 01:55:51.634
- Here he is.
- HICCUP: What is it?

01:55:51.772 --> 01:55:53.325
What is it, huh?

01:55:53.463 --> 01:55:55.638
- Want to take it for a spin?
- [squeals excitedly]

01:55:55.776 --> 01:55:57.951
♪ ♪

01:56:06.338 --> 01:56:08.823
HICCUP:
<i>This is Berk.</i>

01:56:10.756 --> 01:56:12.827
<i>You’d have to be crazy</i>
<i>to move here.</i>

01:56:14.484 --> 01:56:16.624
<i>Even crazier to stay.</i>

01:56:18.592 --> 01:56:21.250
<i>It’s not for</i>
<i>the faint of heart.</i>

01:56:24.667 --> 01:56:26.565
Whoo! [laughs]

01:56:26.703 --> 01:56:28.498
HICCUP:
<i>Any food that grows here</i>

01:56:28.636 --> 01:56:30.845
<i>is tough and tasteless.</i>

01:56:30.984 --> 01:56:32.502
Come on!

01:56:32.640 --> 01:56:34.194
HICCUP:
<i>The people that grow here...</i>

01:56:34.332 --> 01:56:35.989
- Whoa!
<i>- ...are even more so.</i>

01:56:36.127 --> 01:56:38.025
[laughing]

01:56:39.544 --> 01:56:43.306
<i> </i><i>The only upsides are the pets.</i>

01:56:43.444 --> 01:56:46.758
<i>While other places may have</i>
<i>ponies or puppies...</i>

01:56:46.896 --> 01:56:50.106
- Come on, bud.
<i>- ...we have...</i>

01:56:50.244 --> 01:56:52.764
[dragons roaring]

01:56:52.902 --> 01:56:54.628
<i>...dragons.</i>

01:56:54.766 --> 01:56:56.975
♪ ♪

01:57:05.535 --> 01:57:08.987
["You Are My Homeward" playing,
rousing orchestral backing]

01:57:24.416 --> 01:57:27.281
♪ Luck, how she favors me ♪

01:57:27.419 --> 01:57:30.284
♪ Through cold
and stormy seas ♪

01:57:30.422 --> 01:57:33.839
♪ To reach
such wond’rous sights ♪

01:57:33.977 --> 01:57:36.566
♪ I travel always forward ♪

01:57:36.704 --> 01:57:40.570
♪ Ho, where the dragons play ♪

01:57:40.708 --> 01:57:43.228
♪ No harm shall come our way ♪

01:57:43.366 --> 01:57:45.437
♪ We sail for another day ♪

01:57:45.575 --> 01:57:49.924
♪ Fare thee well,
you are my homeward ♪

01:58:04.939 --> 01:58:07.908
♪ Love, you shall always be ♪

01:58:08.046 --> 01:58:10.980
♪ The loving arms for me ♪

01:58:11.118 --> 01:58:14.328
♪ No treasure can compare ♪

01:58:14.466 --> 01:58:18.091
♪ No hardships make me
falter yet ♪

01:58:18.229 --> 01:58:20.438
♪ Do not shed a tear ♪

01:58:20.576 --> 01:58:23.786
♪ Bid me farewell, my dear ♪

01:58:23.924 --> 01:58:26.099
♪ Fear not
for my heart lies here ♪

01:58:26.237 --> 01:58:29.516
♪ I return
for you are my homeward ♪

01:58:29.654 --> 01:58:32.864
♪ You are bringing
me homeward ♪

01:58:33.002 --> 01:58:35.832
♪ You are bringing me home. ♪

01:58:42.632 --> 01:58:44.531
[song ends]

01:58:44.669 --> 01:58:47.120
♪ ♪

01:59:15.976 --> 01:59:18.151
♪ ♪

01:59:52.668 --> 01:59:54.842
♪ ♪

02:00:19.073 --> 02:00:21.248
♪ ♪

02:00:45.617 --> 02:00:47.792
♪ ♪

02:01:20.273 --> 02:01:22.447
♪ ♪

02:01:51.304 --> 02:01:53.444
♪ ♪

02:02:26.615 --> 02:02:28.789
♪ ♪

02:02:57.024 --> 02:03:00.373
[choir singing faintly under
dramatic orchestral score]

02:03:29.229 --> 02:03:31.404
♪ ♪

02:04:02.262 --> 02:04:05.265
[slow, somber version of
"You Are My Homeward" playing]

02:04:07.129 --> 02:04:09.442
♪ Love ♪

02:04:09.580 --> 02:04:14.274
♪ You shall always be ♪

02:04:14.412 --> 02:04:21.350
♪ The loving arms for me ♪

02:04:21.488 --> 02:04:27.943
♪ No treasure can compare ♪

02:04:28.081 --> 02:04:30.324
♪ No hardships ♪

02:04:30.463 --> 02:04:35.882
♪ Make me falter yet ♪

02:04:36.020 --> 02:04:40.369
♪ Do not shed a tear ♪

02:04:40.507 --> 02:04:47.410
♪ Bid me farewell, my dear ♪

02:04:47.549 --> 02:04:50.034
♪ Fear not ♪

02:04:50.172 --> 02:04:53.693
♪ For my heart lies here ♪

02:04:53.831 --> 02:04:55.695
♪ I return ♪

02:04:55.833 --> 02:05:01.908
♪ For you are my homeward ♪

02:05:02.046 --> 02:05:07.051
♪ You are bringing me ♪

02:05:07.189 --> 02:05:13.333
♪ Homeward. ♪

02:05:13.471 --> 02:05:15.646
[song ends]
